INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('328', '70', '3', 'Siem Reap – Rolous Group – Banteay Srei (B/L/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Meet our tour guide and driver at your hotel and enjoy a trip to <strong>Rolous Group</strong>. This is the ancient capital of King Indravarman I during 877AD &ndash; 889AD, also known as the birth place of the classical Khmer art and Architecture.<br />\r\nAmong the <strong>Roluos Group temples</strong>, there are some of the earliest permanent structures built by the Khmer empire, dating from the late 9th century. Some were totally built with bricks, others built with laterite or sandstone.<br />\r\nIn the afternoon, visit<strong> Bantey Srei temple </strong>known as the <strong>Women&rsquo;s citadel </strong>and a cradle of the Angkor&rsquo;s finest stone carving.<br />\r\nThe temple is a masterpiece built with red sandstone.<br />\r\nReturn to Siem Reap and relax</p>\r\n', null, 'dc07a4e96c761f68dbdc3088944ab76b.jpg', '2018-05-29 07:34:57', '2017-11-14 20:45:38', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('329', '70', '4', 'Siem Reap –Tonle Sap Lake – Battambang(B/-/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Transfer to<strong> Tonle Sap Lake</strong>, located 10km from the city center. On arrival, <strong>embark a boat </strong>and discover the largest fresh water lake in Southeast Asia, known as one of the world&rsquo;s most varied and productive ecosystems the region that has always been of central importance for <strong>Cambodia&#39;s food provision.</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nDiscover the beauty of the water landscape and local life on the lake, visit a<strong> floating village</strong> and enjoy the encounters with the locals.<br />\r\nDepart to<strong> Battambang</strong>, and on arrival, visit the village of <strong>Wat Kor</strong>, located about 2km from the town of Battambang. The peculiarity of this village is that it has kept the old wooden houses on stilts of different styles according to the years when they were built and according to the colonizers of the time, the French or Thai.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nYou will have the opportunity to meet the owners of some of these houses who will tell you the <strong>story of their house </strong>and <strong>their ancestors</strong>, in French or English, by showing you every room in their house.&nbsp;<br />\r\nCheck in to your hotel in Battambang and relax.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', null, '39bef9b923bfaad8ca00dd70615a791d.jpg', '2018-05-29 07:36:40', '2017-11-14 20:46:41', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('330', '70', '5', 'Battambang Tour (B/L/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Battambang is the second largest city in Cambodia. It is <strong>surrounded by countryside.</strong> This is a pleasant city that combines modernity and the charm of the best preserved colonial architecture.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe start with a tour to discover its <strong>colonial buildings</strong> and its market, followed by temple <strong>Prasat Banon</strong> 30 km from the city center. Dating back to the 11th century, with five towers and very beautiful engravings, it was an inspiration for the construction of<strong> Angkor temples</strong>. 358 steps lead us to the temple on the top of a mountain to enjoy a panoramic view over the surrounding area.<br />\r\nLunch is served at the local restaurant.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAfter lunch, transfer to <strong>Odam Bang village,</strong> where we&#39;ll enjoy a small bamboo train ride to <strong>Ousrolao village.</strong> It will take almost 2 hours to go there and back. We will visit villages and meet the local people to experience their lifestyle and understand their culture. We return to <strong>Odam Bang village</strong> by the same small train.<br />\r\nThen return to the town by our car and stay overnight in Battambang.</p>\r\n', null, '7fab4168e97eeb52bc5413ea42dd0549.jpg', '2018-05-29 07:36:57', '2017-11-14 20:47:31', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('331', '70', '6', 'Battambang – transfer to Phnom Penh (B/L/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">After breakfast, <strong>transfer to Phnom Penh</strong> by car.<br />\r\n<strong>Lunch</strong> will be served at a local restaurant. On the way, we could make some stops to relax and enjoy the beautiful landscapes on either side of the road.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDiscover the <strong>sculpture workshops </strong>of Art objects and marble Buddha in Pursat and then visit a <strong>pottery village</strong> in Kampong Chhnang.<br />\r\nArrive in Phnom Penh in the afternoon, check in to your hotel and relax.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', null, '3107f1918fa91eecff2ca623d0d3f0b7.jpg', '2018-05-29 07:37:16', '2017-11-14 20:47:54', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('332', '70', '7', 'Phnom Penh – Full Day city Tour (B/-/-)', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Breakfast at hotel, Spend a full day to learn about the<strong> Khmer rouge</strong> in the past and Cambodia in the present.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn the morning, start to visit the impressive<strong> colorful Khmer-style royal palace complex</strong> build in 1866 by the Predecessors of King Norodom. Nearby is <strong>Silver pagoda </strong>(the emerald Buddha temple), where contain plenty of Buddha Statues decorated and made by gold, diamond, gemstones and silver. Then visit the <strong>National Museum.</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nFollowed by a visit to <strong>Choeung Ek museum or Killing field </strong>where about 17 000 innocent Cambodian people (during1975 and 1978) including men, women, children and infants detained and tortured at S-21 prison were transported for the extermination.<br />\r\nWe continue to <strong>Tuol Sleng prison</strong> now is <strong>Genocide Museum</strong>, the most secret part of the Khmer Rouge regime. It&rsquo;s also called S-21 (abbreviated for Security Office 21), a Khmer Rouge&#39;s premier security camp, specifically designed for the interrogation and extermination of anti-Angkor elements.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nSurprised to know that S 21 use to be a high school before becoming a terrible place in the world during Khmer Rouge regime.<br />\r\nBack to the city to discover the local daily life at <strong>Russian market</strong>, enjoy the bustling daily activities of the locals.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nOvernight in Phnom Penh.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', null, '2b1f5797e528a12f66226b7020ddee90.jpg', '2017-11-15 03:48:52', '2017-11-14 20:48:52', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('333', '70', '8', 'Phnom Penh – Departure (B/-/-)', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Free till meet our driver for a <strong>transfer to airport</strong> for your <strong>next destinations or flight home.</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nTour ends.</p>\r\n', null, '4db792d1762083680e984ca0d5472ec0.jpg', '2017-11-15 03:49:12', '2017-11-14 20:49:12', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('334', '71', '1', 'Phnom Penh arrival (-/-/D)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Upon arrival, our Authentik Travel tour guide will <strong>welcome you </strong>at the international airport and <strong>transfer</strong> you a short distance to the city center. Check in at your hotel and enjoy a <strong>briefing tour</strong> as well as some first information about this beautiful region.<br />\r\n<strong>A welcome dinner</strong> will be served in the finest restaurant in the city.<br />\r\nStay overnight in Phnom Penh.</p>\r\n', null, 'db3751e6ce1bc62dc9ca946e40a4076c.jpg', '2018-05-25 07:46:16', '2017-11-14 20:29:13', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('335', '71', '2', 'Phnom Penh city tour (B/-/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Have breakfast at your hotel, then spend a full day learning about the <strong>Khmer rouge</strong> in the past and Cambodia in the present.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn the morning, start with a visit to the <strong>impressive colorful Khmer-style royal palace</strong> complex built in 1866 by the Predecessors of King Norodom. Nearby is <strong>Silver pagoda </strong>(the emerald Buddha temple), which contains plenty of decorated Buddha Statues made of gold, diamond, gemstones and silver. Then visit the <strong>National Museum.</strong><br />\r\nFollow this by visiting <strong>Choeung Ek museum</strong> or the<strong> Killing fields</strong>, where about 17 000 innocent Cambodian people (during1975 and 1978) including men, women, children and infants were detained and tortured at S-21 prison then transported for their extermination.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe continue to <strong>Tuol Sleng prison</strong>, now the <strong>Genocide Museum</strong>, the most secret part of the Khmer Rouge regime. It&rsquo;s also called<strong> S-21</strong> (abbreviated for Security Office 21), Khmer Rouge&#39;s premier security camp, specifically designed for the interrogation and extermination of anti-Angkor elements.<br />\r\nIt&#39;s surprising to know that S-21 used to be a high school before becoming this awful place during Khmer Rouge regime.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nReturn to the city to discover the local daily life at the <strong>Russian market</strong> and enjoy the bustling daily activities of the locals.&nbsp;<br />\r\nGo back to your hotel and relax.<br />\r\nNote: Please consider a different trip to the killing fields and S2-1 prison if you have small children in the group. We will offer other suitable alternative programs such as <strong>Koh Dach Island or Tamao wildlife </strong>rescue center.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', null, '4db792d1762083680e984ca0d5472ec0.jpg', '2018-05-25 09:30:34', '2017-11-14 20:30:33', '5', '5');
