INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('360', '75', '2', 'Vientiane full day city tour - Flight to Xieng Khuang (B/-/-)', '<p>Enjoy your breakfast at hotel and meet our tour guide for<strong> full day Vientiane city exploration.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The first highlight of the trip is <strong>Vat Phra Keo temple</strong>, built in 1565. It is one of the most interesting and impressive temples in Vientiane. It previously housed the famous <strong>Emerald Buddha image</strong>.<br />\r\nNext, visit <strong>Vat Sisaket temple</strong> which is well known for not only its cloister wall storing thousands of small Buddha images but also its beautiful architecture and decoration with dating back to 1818.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Transfer to visit <strong>Pha That Luang temple</strong>, built in 1566 and reconstructed in 1930. It is the most important Laotian religious and national monument. The temple has a special architecture reflecting the culture and identity of Laos, becoming a symbol of Laos nationalism.<br />\r\nLater, discover the<strong> Patuxay arc</strong>, a memorial monument built in 1957 and the most prominent landmark in the city. Its architecture was inspired by the &#39;<strong>Arc de Triumph&#39; in Paris</strong> combined with typical Laotian style. From the top of the monument, you can enjoy a great panoramic view of the city.<br />\r\nNext, move to <strong>Talat Sao market</strong> where you can do some shopping and uncover the local life.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">In the afternoon, take a <strong>short flight to Xieng Khuang</strong> airport.<br />\r\nOn arrival, get a pick up to hotel.<br />\r\nOvernight in Xieng Khuang.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', null, '1ead6a12e1197201481385041aca58e8.jpg', '2018-05-18 08:55:22', '2017-11-15 20:14:32', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('361', '75', '3', 'Xieng Khuang – Plain of Jar (B/-/-)', '<p>After breakfast at your hotel, enjoy a short trek to explore the <strong>mysterious Plain of Jars</strong> and the surrounding area.<br />\r\nThe jars are supposed to be 2000 years old, although there is little proof to date them accurately.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nNowadays, archaeologist still struggle to find the <strong>specific purpose of the jars</strong>. Were they used for funerary urns or to store rice wine? It remains a question without any answer. Observe local village life, visit a <strong>small monastery</strong> in <strong>Ban Xiengdi </strong>and pass through areas that used to be important <strong>battlefields during the American war</strong>.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nContinue to <strong>Muang Khoun</strong>, the one place in the old provincial capital that was not destroyed by American bombings.<br />\r\nStay overnight in Xieng Khuang.</p>\r\n', null, 'eb6839cfbcc76baa158e3b05fe079a20.jpg', '2018-05-18 08:56:58', '2017-11-15 20:15:32', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('362', '75', '4', 'Xieng Khoang – Transfer to Luang Prabang (B/-/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Enjoy your breakfast, take a 6 hour driving to<strong> Luang Prabang </strong>with&nbsp; some stops and &nbsp;lunch at <strong>Sala Phoukhou</strong>.<br />\r\nAfter lunch we continue on our way to Luang Prabang via Road 13 whilst enjoying the beautiful landscapes along the road.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nUpon arrival, check in hotel and climb up to <strong>Phousi hill</strong> to enjoy the panorama view of Luang Prabang town.<br />\r\nReturn to the town and discover the <strong>night market</strong>&nbsp;on&nbsp;your own.<br />\r\nOvernight in Luang Prabang.</p>\r\n', null, 'd240c4f42d9503437f9a525aeb809cac.jpg', '2018-05-18 08:57:41', '2017-11-15 20:16:07', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('363', '75', '5', 'Luang Prabang – City Tour – Pak Ou cave (B/-/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">After breakfast at your hotel, meet our tour guide and driver to go to <strong>Mount Phousi</strong> where you can enjoy a great panoramic view of the City and the river.<br />\r\nTake a short drive to <strong>Vat Xien Thong</strong> (the temple of Royal city). This is one of the most important Laotian monasteries and still remains a significant monument to the spirit of religion, traditional art and royalty.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe next&nbsp; stop will be <strong>Wat Visoun temple</strong>, dating back to 1513 and the reign of <strong>King Visoun</strong> . This is the oldest temple in Luang Prabang and was once the home to Luang Prabang Buddhas. <strong>Wat Visoun temple </strong>is with an unusual structure which represents the earliest Laotian style.<br />\r\nFollow this with a visit to <strong>Wat Mai</strong>, a beautiful temple built in the 18th century, located by the Royal palace. It is the biggest temple in Luang Prabang with beautiful decorations.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nEnjoy a boat trip along the <strong>Pak Oo River </strong>to discover the peaceful landscapes and the numerous Buddha images in the <strong>Pak Oo caves </strong>such as <strong>Pak Oo cave</strong> (the mouth of the Oo River), <strong>Tham Ting cave</strong> (Lower cave) and <strong>Tham Theung</strong> (Upper cave). Then, walk around <strong>Ban Pak Ou Village</strong>, a small Laotian fishermen&rsquo;s village on the Mekong River, and continue to <strong>Ban MuangKeo village</strong>, where you will see the production of colored fabric, which is woven on simple <strong>weaving looms</strong>.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFinally, return to LuangPrabang by boat.<br />\r\nOvernight in Luang Prabang.</p>\r\n', null, 'a295fd9c4f9e379407970942be7594be.jpg', '2018-05-18 09:09:36', '2017-11-15 20:17:34', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('364', '75', '6', 'Luang Prabang – Khuang Si fall (B/-/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Breakfast at hotel and explore the life style at local market in the morning.<br />\r\nEnjoy a driving through<strong> rice fields</strong> and a <strong>beautiful small village</strong>. Make some stops to discover their daily life before reaching <strong>Khuang Si fall</strong>, a gorgeous turquoise waterfall. Refresh and swim in the clear water.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nReturn to city and spend the <strong>rest of day at your leisure.</strong><br />\r\nStay overnight at a hotel in Luang Prabang.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', null, '6f0a59c65ebe0ee9ae3dee45e9fe9220.jpg', '2018-05-18 09:10:55', '2017-11-15 20:18:06', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('365', '75', '7', 'Luang Prabang – Departure (B/-/-)', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Free on your own till meet your driver for a<strong> transfer to airport </strong>for<strong> your flight home </strong>or next destinations.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTour ends.</p>\r\n', null, 'be5f2fe38e29e00b8d8eb9f5cbb68517.jpg', '2017-11-16 03:18:59', '2017-11-15 20:18:59', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('366', '76', '1', 'Huay Xai – Luang Nam Tha (-/-/-)', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Our local tour guide will <strong>welcome</strong> and transfer you to <strong>Luang Nam Tha</strong> - a capital of the same name province. It is particularly quiet and relaxing, and generally represents an essential stop for those wishing to discover the natural wealth in the region of northwestern Laos.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nArea <strong>Muang Nam Tha</strong> presents some points of interest: the museum of<strong> Luang Nam Tha</strong>, containing articles and a local section devoted to the revolution. <strong>Night market</strong> is a great place to taste the local foods.<br />\r\nIn addition, Luang Nam Tha city is interested with the<strong> That Phum Puk stupa</strong>, perched on a hill surrounded by <strong>rice fields, and a waterfall</strong>, accessible from the <strong>Nam Sun village</strong> where you can see the process of <strong>bamboo papermaking</strong>. The region is famous for its huge evergreen forests, an ideal place for ecotourism.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAccommodation is at the <strong>Boat Landing Guest House,</strong> located in a pleasant environment along the river.</p>\r\n', null, 'a75880feb25c27ec0cf4f22779b702ab.jpg', '2017-11-16 02:55:30', '2017-11-15 19:55:30', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('367', '76', '2', 'Luang Nam Tha – Trekking – Vieng Phoukha - Ban Nam O - Ban Nam Lo (B/L/D)', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">After breakfast, take a half a hour<strong> riding by Tuk-Tuk to Doiluckkam</strong>, where a local Khmu guide will join you on your journey.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe first day&rsquo;s trekking pace is moderate through the <strong>Nam Ha NPA</strong> where the guide will show you the edible and medicinal plants.<br />\r\nThen you will trek uphill and see some massive old trees, many types of bamboo and diverse forest plants. If lucky, you may see some wild animals such as: monkeys, wild goats and wild pigs. Our Khmu local guide will prepare the traditional picnic lunch.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAfter lunch, keep continue our <strong>trekking down from the mountain to your jungle camp</strong>, which we should reach by 4:30 pm, spending a night near the <strong>Nam Ha River</strong>. Besides resting, you are free to go fishing for dinner with your Khmu guide, stroll around the camp or enjoy a swim in the Nam Ha River close to your <strong>Jungle camp.</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nOvernight in Jungle Camp<br />\r\nTrekking 5 hours.</p>\r\n', null, 'ff63353bf7a4f5e8268ad545fcf23ec9.jpg', '2017-11-16 02:59:36', '2017-11-15 19:59:36', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('368', '76', '3', 'Ban Nam Lo - Prasat Cave - Vieng Phoukha - Oudomxay (B/L/-)', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Enjoy the natural sounds</strong> in the early morning such as:, monkeys, wild pigs, barking deer, gibbons, and jungle fowl from the higher mountain.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nYou might be very fortunate if you spot some moving through the forest. Before breakfast, you are <strong>free to walk around the camp.</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast at camping, you&rsquo;ll <strong>cross the Nam Ha River</strong> and walk through fields to reach and <strong>visit Ban Nalan</strong>, where your will learn about Khmu lifestyle, culture, and traditions.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTreking uphill to the forest, traditional lunch will be served en route on the forest path. Thereafter, you will have an easy two hour <strong>hiking down the mountain slope</strong> until you arrive at the B<strong>an Chalernsouk,</strong> where our driver will be waiting for you and transfer you to <strong>Oudomxay.</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nOvernight at a guesthouse in Oudomxay.<br />\r\nTrekking 4 hours.</p>\r\n', null, '3778b26f61fd67409d63d23594cdace3.jpg', '2017-11-16 03:02:01', '2017-11-15 20:02:01', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('369', '76', '4', 'Oudomxay – Muang Khua – Muang Ngoi (B/L/D)', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">After breakfast, leaving Oudomxay for <strong>Muang Khua</strong> in the morning.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nContinue<strong> our trip by boat cruise to Muong Ngoi</strong> (4-5 hours on board) . Muong Ngoi is one hour driving north of <strong>Nong Khiaw.</strong> The village is small and narrow paths lined with coconut trees and a common area where fishermen gather to mend their nets. It is really true lifestyle Laos in here. Time seems to have stopped.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nOvernight in local guesthouse in Muang Ngoi.<br />\r\nOudomxay &ndash; Muang Khua: 100km &ndash; 1.5 hours<br />\r\nMuang Khua &ndash; Muang Ngoi: by Private Boat 3.5 hours.</p>\r\n', null, '23ca365326b229d0ed33a9aca5d5af04.jpg', '2017-11-16 03:02:58', '2017-11-15 20:02:58', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('370', '76', '5', 'Muang Ngoi – Nong Khaiw (B/L/-)', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Enjoy your breakfast at hotel and transfer to the pier for a <strong>boat trip to Nong Khaiw.</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nFollowing a lunch and<strong> visit the historical Phathok cave</strong>. The local Nong Khaiw villagers used this cave for as the shelter during the &ldquo;secret war&rdquo; to avoid from the bombing. The cave is only 30 minute walk from the town Nong Khaiw town and during the walk, immerse into the beautiful scenery and gorgeous vistas in the surrounding tropical mountains. From the cave, you will have a <strong>great view to the rice paddies and the valley</strong>, listening to the Laos history and explore the historical cave.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Enjoy a great sunset</strong> over the river.<br />\r\nBack to Nong Khiaw town and overnight there.</p>\r\n', null, 'a37a9d3780f5bc21a1eca99d4e425a1f.jpg', '2017-11-16 03:03:38', '2017-11-15 20:03:38', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('371', '76', '6', 'Nong  Khaiw – Pak Ou cave – Luang Prabang (B/-/-)', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Get up to enjoy the atmosphere in this peaceful town and breakfast before driving down south to <strong>Luang Prabang</strong>. Passing the picturesque scenery along the <strong>Nam Ou River.</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nAfter lunch, embark a <strong>boat trip to Luang Prabang</strong> and visit the <strong>Pak Ou caves</strong> at the confluence of the Nam Ou River and Mekong River. The cave is home to a pantheon of gold Buddha statues tucked into the nooks of the limestone cliffs. It is then only a short distance to visit from the caves to the village of<strong> Ban Xang Hai.</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Encounter the locals</strong> and learn <strong>how to make LauLao (Laos whisky) and LauHai (Laos wine)</strong>. &nbsp;Continuing down the Mekong to Luang Prabang. Check in at the hotel then take an evening stroll through the quaint streets and <strong>enjoy the sunset over the river </strong>and surrounding lush countryside.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe evening highlight includes a visit to the<strong> local night market </strong>in the city center, where ethnic minority people come together to buy and sell their wares.<br />\r\nOvernight in Luang Prabang.</p>\r\n', null, 'a5b2271bf127c1f65ea0b8970b8f484a.jpg', '2017-11-16 03:10:01', '2017-11-15 20:10:01', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('372', '76', '7', 'Luang Prabang – City tour – Khuang Si Fall (B/-/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">After breakfast at your hotel, meet our tour guide and driver to go to <strong>Mount Phousi</strong> where you can enjoy a great panoramic view of the City and the river.<br />\r\nTake a short drive to <strong>Vat Xien Thong</strong> (the temple of Royal city). This is one of the most important Laotian monasteries and still remains a significant monument to the spirit of religion, traditional art and royalty.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe next&nbsp; stop will be <strong>Wat Visoun temple</strong>, dating back to 1513 and the reign of <strong>King Visoun</strong> . This is the oldest temple in Luang Prabang and was once the home to Luang Prabang Buddhas. <strong>Wat Visoun temple </strong>is with an unusual structure which represents the earliest Laotian style.<br />\r\nFollow this with a visit to <strong>Wat Mai</strong>, a beautiful temple built in the 18th century, located by the Royal palace. It is the biggest temple in Luang Prabang with beautiful decorations.<br />\r\nEnjoy a driving through rice fields and a beautiful small village. Make some stops to discover their daily life before reaching<strong> Khuang Si fall,</strong> a gorgeous turquoise waterfall. <strong>Refresh and swim</strong> in the clear water.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nReturn to city and spend the rest of day at your leisure.<br />\r\nStay overnight at a hotel in Luang Prabang.</p>\r\n', null, 'ccceee0527a1dfaf4a79e09ecb1c1584.jpg', '2018-05-18 07:41:28', '2017-11-15 20:11:28', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('373', '76', '8', 'Luang Prabang Departure (B/-/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Enjoy your breakfast at hotel, relax or <strong>explore the town on your own</strong> at last minute before meet our driver for a <strong>transfer to airport</strong> for your <strong>flight home</strong> or next destinations.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTour ends.</p>\r\n', null, '8ac822b8b728f299b9ffb4faef4c3f7d.jpg', '2018-05-18 07:41:39', '2017-11-15 20:11:51', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('374', '77', '1', 'Luang Prabang arrival (-/-/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Upon Luang Prabang airport, our Authenik Travel&rsquo;s tour guide and driver <strong>will welcome </strong>you and<strong> transfer to your hotel </strong>in the city center.<br />\r\nMeals on your own and take a rest after your flight.<br />\r\nOvernight in Luang Prabang.</p>\r\n', null, '0fd13f28d85c04f67768cc5a0b6035e5.jpg', '2018-05-18 07:18:23', '2017-11-15 19:39:54', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('375', '77', '2', 'Luang Prabang city tour – Khuang Si fall (B/-/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">After breakfast at your hotel, meet our tour guide and driver to go to <strong>Mount Phousi</strong> where you can enjoy a great panoramic view of the City and the river.<br />\r\nTake a short drive to <strong>Vat Xien Thong</strong> (the temple of Royal city). This is one of the most important Laotian monasteries and still remains a significant monument to the spirit of religion, traditional art and royalty.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe next&nbsp; stop will be <strong>Wat Visoun temple</strong>, dating back to 1513 and the reign of <strong>King Visoun</strong> . This is the oldest temple in Luang Prabang and was once the home to Luang Prabang Buddhas. <strong>Wat Visoun temple </strong>is with an unusual structure which represents the earliest Laotian style.<br />\r\nFollow this with a visit to <strong>Wat Mai</strong>, a beautiful temple built in the 18th century, located by the Royal palace. It is the biggest temple in Luang Prabang with beautiful decorations.<br />\r\nEnjoy a driving through rice fields and a beautiful small village. Make some stops to discover their daily life before reaching<strong> Khuang Si fall,</strong> a gorgeous turquoise waterfall. <strong>Refresh and swim</strong> in the clear water.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nReturn to city and spend the rest of day at your leisure.<br />\r\nStay overnight at a hotel in Luang Prabang.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', null, 'ccceee0527a1dfaf4a79e09ecb1c1584.jpg', '2018-05-18 07:20:40', '2017-11-15 19:41:28', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('376', '77', '3', 'Luang Prabang – Pak Ou cave (B/L/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Have breakfast at your hotel then visit a <strong>local market</strong> in the town to discover the daily life. (We recommend visiting early in the morning).<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTransfer to the pier, embark a <strong>boat and enjoy a trip</strong> upstream along the Mekong River. Discover the <strong>numerous Buddha images in the Pak Oo caves </strong>such as <strong>Pak Oo cave</strong> (the mouth of the Oo River), <strong>Tham Ting cave</strong> ( Lower cave) and <strong>Tham Theung</strong> ( Upper cave). They are on the right side and overlook the Mekong River. Travel a short distance from the caves to the village of <strong>Ban Xang Hai</strong>.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nEncounter the locals and learn how to make LauLao (Laotian whisky) and <strong>LauHa</strong>i (Laotian wine). Return to the city, making stops at &nbsp;<strong>Ban Xang Khong village</strong> and <strong>Ban Xieng Lek village</strong>, well known for handmade <strong>Jute Sar paper</strong>.<br />\r\nReturn to your hotel and relax and stay overnight in Luang Prabang.</p>\r\n', null, 'a295fd9c4f9e379407970942be7594be.jpg', '2018-05-18 07:29:47', '2017-11-15 19:43:14', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('377', '77', '4', 'Luang Prabang – Khmu Village visit – fly to Vientiane (B/L/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">In the morning, meet our tour guide at your hotel and you cross the <strong>Mekong River</strong> via a local ferry towards <strong>Khmu village</strong>. En route, make a short visit to <strong>Ban Chan pottery village</strong>. It is a rare chance to try your hand at creating beautiful pots from clay.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAlong the way, you will pass through some <strong>rustic villages</strong>, encounter the local people, and see the children playing together or farmers doing their work on the fields. <strong>Visit Ban Boum Xieng</strong> to observe the ethnic traditions and daily life. Continue driving to a <strong>Khmu family</strong> and enjoy lunch with them.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn the afternoon, drive back to the Mekong River and discover the decorative, less visited <strong>Wat Long Khun temple</strong>. From here, take a short transfer to <strong>Wat Tham Xieng Maen</strong> located in a limestone cave and visit its Buddha images.&nbsp;<br />\r\nThe last highlight of the day is<strong> Wat Chom phet</strong> - This is an excellent spot for a panoramic view of the area.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nBack to the city and transfer to airport for <strong>short flight to Vientiane.</strong><br />\r\nUpon arrival, pick up to hotel, check in and free to relax.<br />\r\nOvernight in Vientiane.</p>\r\n', null, '18853fbc11aa9a1c6dd86db0bd1aaa1b.jpg', '2018-05-18 07:31:43', '2017-11-15 19:45:40', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('378', '77', '5', 'Vientiane city tour – Buddha Park (B/-/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Enjoy your breakfast at hotel and meet our tour guide for<strong> full day Vientiane city exploration.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The first highlight of the trip is <strong>Vat Phra Keo temple</strong>, built in 1565. It is one of the most interesting and impressive temples in Vientiane. It previously housed the famous <strong>Emerald Buddha image</strong>.<br />\r\nNext, visit <strong>Vat Sisaket temple</strong> which is well known for not only its cloister wall storing thousands of small Buddha images but also its beautiful architecture and decoration with dating back to 1818.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Transfer to visit <strong>Pha That Luang temple</strong>, built in 1566 and reconstructed in 1930. It is the most important Laotian religious and national monument. The temple has a special architecture reflecting the culture and identity of Laos, becoming a symbol of Laos nationalism.<br />\r\nLater, discover the<strong> Patuxay arc</strong>, a memorial monument built in 1957 and the most prominent landmark in the city. Its architecture was inspired by the &#39;<strong>Arc de Triumph&#39; in Paris</strong> combined with typical Laotian style. From the top of the monument, you can enjoy a great panoramic view of the city.<br />\r\nNext, move to <strong>Talat Sao market</strong> where you can do some shopping and uncover the local life.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the afternoon, visit the famous<strong> Buddha Park</strong>, located 25km from the city. The park is home to over 200 Buddha statues and characters of Hinduism made from concrete, especially the enormous Buddha statue which is 40m in length propping its arm. Furthermore, there are many other statues you could visit to understand more about Buddhism.<br />\r\nStay overnight in Vientiane</p>\r\n', null, '1ead6a12e1197201481385041aca58e8.jpg', '2018-05-18 07:35:31', '2017-11-15 19:48:31', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('379', '77', '6', 'Vientiane – Fly to Pakse – Bolaven (B/-/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Meet our driver at hotel and transfer to the airport without guide to catch your short <strong>flight to Pakse.</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nUpon arrival at Pakse airport, our guide and driver will welcome you and continue the trip to <strong>Bolaven Plateau</strong>, located in the east of Pakse. It is home to <strong>various hill tribes and great of beautiful landscape</strong> as well as countless waterfalls.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nStop to visit<strong> Tad Lo waterfalls</strong> featuring crystalline water. In the afternoon, keep continue to <strong>Tad Yuang &amp; Tad Fane waterfalls</strong>, stopping en-route to<strong> visit a coffee, tea plantation.</strong><br />\r\nOvernight in Bolaven Plateau.</p>\r\n', null, '7cc9df45fbfc457d0276d9e63f531b2d.jpg', '2018-05-18 07:36:28', '2017-11-15 19:49:59', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('380', '77', '7', 'Bolaven – Wat Phou temple – Khon Phapheng – 4000 islands (B/-/-)', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">We leave Bolaven for <strong>4000 islands</strong> in the morning by our private car, on the way, stop to visit<strong> Vat Phou ruin temple.</strong> Recognized by UNESCO as the World Heritage. Wat Phou is a grandiose pre-angkorian temple built upon three levels.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nExplore<strong> Ou Mong Ruins</strong> before driving to <strong>Khone Papheng </strong>- one of the most significant attractions of the 4000 islands. This 10 kilometer waterfall becomes the largest waterfall in Southeast Asia and considered the gem of Laos.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDriving to the biggest island of <strong>Si Phan Done </strong>area - <strong>Don Khong</strong>. Enjoy the stunning views of water whilst relaxing at hotel.<br />\r\nOvernight in Don Khong.</p>\r\n', null, 'df4be137da686711c20ab0da5d23eaf5.jpg', '2017-11-16 02:50:41', '2017-11-15 19:50:41', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('381', '77', '8', '4000 Islands – Pakse (B/-/-)', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Explore the 2 islands <strong>Don Det and Don Khone</strong>. Take a boat trip along Mekong River. Enjoy the beautiful landscape of the river and see the local people&rsquo;s daily life as well as the peaceful time to see the children playing along the Mekong River.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Take a bike to visit </strong>these two islands, which are linked by a bridge. <strong>Visit Ban Khone fishing village</strong> - where you could explore the ruins of<strong> French railway tracks</strong> and the beautiful<strong> Liphi Waterfall.</strong> Enjoy the tranquil atmosphere in the islands and capture the great photos of the local life and natural beauty.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In the afternoon, enjoy the boat trip again to visit the River along Cambodian border where the famous Irrawaddy dolphins live. If lucky, you can see them playing and swim on the river.<br />\r\n<strong>Transfer to Pakse for leisure.</strong><br />\r\nOvernight in Pakse.</p>\r\n', null, '30184a12ac44e2151e21a92e91cd3707.jpg', '2017-11-16 02:51:56', '2017-11-15 19:51:56', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('382', '77', '9', 'Pakse (B/-/-)', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Breakfast at the hotel then enjoy your free time before meet our driver for <strong>transfer to the airport </strong>without guide to catch your departure <strong>flight home or next destination.</strong><br />\r\nRoom is your disposal until noon only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTour ends.</p>\r\n', null, '49e49b5a2d73c2264cc711753d35c5fd.jpg', '2017-11-16 02:52:45', '2017-11-15 19:52:45', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('383', '78', '1', 'Hanoi arrival – walking tour (-/-/D)', '<p><strong>Be welcomed</strong> at the airport by our Authentik Travel&#39;s tour guide&nbsp;and<strong> transfer to your hotel</strong> in the city center.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Check in at your hotel (after 12:00pm) or leave your luggage at the hotel and enjoy a<strong> walk in the old quarter</strong>. The city was built in the 10<sup>th</sup> century by the villagers near the <strong>Red River Delta</strong>. You can see the special architecture in the houses with their narrow width and deep length. You will be able to discover some popular streets such as<strong> Ma May, Hang Ma, Hang Dong, Hang Bac and Hang Gai </strong>and for tourist sites stop at <strong>Dong Xuan market,</strong> the biggest market in the northern Vietnam, <strong>Bach Ma temple</strong> (White horse temple) and the <strong>traditional ancient house</strong> at 87 Ma May Street. Head back to your hotel.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nEnjoy our <strong>welcome dinner </strong>at a finest local restaurant and overnight in Hanoi.</p>\r\n', null, '2ada072300e9d9f02d8c746b452b18e6.jpg', '2018-05-31 09:15:44', '2017-11-14 19:26:31', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('384', '78', '2', 'Hanoi – City Tour – Train to Sapa (B/L/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Today, we discover the wonders of the <strong>capital of Vietnam</strong>, filled with timeless charm. Start by visiting <strong>Van Mieu (Temple of Literature)</strong>, the first University of Vietnam built from the 11th century by Emperor Ly Thanh Tong. Continue to visit <strong>Chua Ha (Ha Pagoda)</strong>, known as a sacred place to pray for luck in love, especially for your future spouse.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAfter that, transfer to the<strong> Ethnology Museum</strong> (closed every Monday) which offers a deep insight into Vietnamese culture through traditional costumes, tools, musical instruments and traditional houses of many minority ethnic groups. Enjoy a special<strong> water puppet show in the museum garden.</strong><br />\r\n<strong>Lunch </strong>is served in a local restaurant.<br />\r\nIn the afternoon, discover the <strong>Ho Chi Minh complex</strong> including the <strong>Presidential Palace, Ho Chi Minh&#39;s House on stilts and the fish pond</strong>.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor those who are interested in visiting the <strong>Ho Chi Minh Mausoleum</strong>, it is only open in the morning and closed every Monday and Friday. Sometimes it is necessary to queue for a couple of hours to go inside the mausoleum.<br />\r\nTransfer to the old quarter to visit Hoan Kiem lake (Restored Sword Lake) and Ngoc Son temple in the middle of the lake. In the late afternoon, take a night train to Sapa.<br />\r\nOvernight on Train (Share 4 Berth AC cabin).</p>\r\n', null, 'd0e99205a6caff33fa0c9606a0b69eba.jpg', '2018-05-31 09:16:05', '2017-11-14 19:27:39', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('385', '78', '3', 'Sapa – Cat Cat – Y Linh Ho – Lao Chai – Ta Van (B/L/-) ', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Arrive in Lao Cai</strong>&nbsp;in the early morning, our local guide will pick you up at the railway station and&nbsp;<strong>transfer to Sapa town.&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nEnjoy breakfast at local restaurant and&nbsp;start a full day of <strong>trekking from Cat Cat Village</strong> of the Black Hmong. Visit its beautiful<strong> waterfall</strong> then follow the path to <strong>Y Linh Ho village.</strong><br />\r\nArrive at<strong> Y Linh Ho bridge</strong>. Stop to relax a little bit then resume trekking along the <strong>buffalo path</strong> through the hills. You will have chance to enjoy the splendid view over the<strong> rice terrace valley</strong> considered one of the most fantastic of the world.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nLunch will be served on the way.<br />\r\nAfter lunch take a short break before trekking to the<strong> Lao Chai village </strong>of the black Hmong and <strong>Ta Van village</strong> of the Zay people.<br />\r\nAt 16.00 meet our driver and transfer to Sapa<br />\r\nOvernight in Sapa.</p>\r\n', null, '796369b3b4e478ae9993ebb1589d7750.jpg', '2018-05-31 09:16:23', '2017-11-14 19:28:46', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('386', '78', '4', 'Sapa Discovery – Night train to Hanoi (B/-/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">After breakfast at your hotel, our guide will meet you for a visit to&nbsp;<strong>Silver Water fall.</strong>&nbsp;This is one of the highest and most beautiful falls in Sapa.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTransfer further 3 km to reach&nbsp;<strong>Tram Ton Pass &ndash; 2000m from the sea level.&nbsp;</strong>You will feel the drop of temperature but the views are so gorgeous.<br />\r\nIt time for you to relax and take photos before driving back to Sapa town for your own lunch, relax then checkout the hotel before exploring the<strong>&nbsp;Dragon Jaw Mountain.</strong>&nbsp;Walking up to the mountain is the way to enjoy the beauty of the landscapes and alot of flowers on the way.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFrom the top of the&nbsp;<strong>Dragon Jaw Mountain</strong>, you will able to view all charming Sapa town&nbsp;and the&nbsp;<strong>Peak of Fansipan from distance.</strong><br />\r\nDinner is on your own then transfer to&nbsp;<strong>Lao Cai railway station for night train to Hanoi.</strong><br />\r\nOvernight on train ( Share 4 berth AC cabin).</p>\r\n', null, '7eb1c7ff4710770ae63a68ed76e52d7e.jpg', '2018-05-31 09:16:40', '2017-11-14 19:30:24', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('387', '78', '5', 'Hanoi – Ninh Binh – Van Long Discover (B/L/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">At 8.00am, meet our tour guide and driver for a transfer from <strong>Hanoi to Ninh Binh</strong>, driving through the picturesque countryside of the <strong>Red River Delta</strong>, painted by rice and vegetable fields.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAfter a 1.5 hour drive, you will arrive in<strong> Van Long </strong>(100km from Hanoi) where you will meet a <strong>typical&nbsp;rural family</strong>. Be welcomed to their home with a <strong>cup of tea</strong> and learn about their idyllic local lifestyles through intimate conversation.<br />\r\nTake a <strong>15km bike ride</strong> ( or by car)&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong>walk through the villages</strong>. A journey along the dyke will offer you gorgeous landscapes of rice fields, a river and limestone mountains. There are several stops for you to take beautiful photos or encounter the locals then walk to discover <strong>Thung La temple</strong>, dating back to the 11th century.&nbsp;Meet Mr Tuong, the temple guardian, and enjoy an authentic conversation as well as a <strong>20 minute drum show.</strong>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nLater, take a <strong>sampan boat trip</strong> along the stream and among the limestone mountains to discover the beauty of <strong>Van Long Nature reserve</strong>. If lucky, you might get to see <strong>white monkeys</strong> and egrets on the cliffs.<br />\r\nAfter the boat trip, visit an <strong>embroidery village</strong> and take part in an embroidery course under the instruction of local craftswoman, Mrs Lam. She will proudly explain the techniques of her traditional craft. This will be a good opportunity for you to practice on fabric like a real craftsman.<br />\r\nOvernight at Hotel in Ninh Binh.</p>\r\n', null, '26239dea9fbb4a3fd0794961558b9bbe.jpg', '2018-05-31 09:17:53', '2017-11-14 19:32:08', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('388', '78', '6', 'Van Long – Thien Ha – Thung Nham – Hanoi (B/L/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Enjoy breakfast at hotel and enjoy a trip to<strong>Thung Nham, Ninh Bin</strong>h through the luxuriant vegetation of the Red River Delta.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nArrive at <strong>Thien Ha Pier</strong> and <strong>embark a small, bamboo sampan boat</strong> to start a fantastic two hour boat trip with a local rower. The trip will lead you into the mystical limestone mountains as the <strong>picturesque rural countryside</strong> unfolds in front of your eyes: <strong>Buffaloes, ducks, and simple houses </strong>under the foot of the mountain all make this an idyllic rural picture.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWalk up to the <strong>Thien Ha cave</strong> (Celestial river Cave). This is a large cave that was only discovered in 2007. It is about 12,000 square meters in total and contains a lot of <strong>magnificent stalagmites and stalactites</strong> with different mystical shapes. Walk for the first 200m then take another boat trip inside the cave to discover its paradisaical beauty.<br />\r\nAfter visiting Thien Ha, travel to Thung Nham. Take a <strong>bike to ride through the rural villages</strong>, limestone mountains and impressive rice paddies to Tam Coc.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Lunch </strong>will be served at a local restaurant.<br />\r\nIn the afternoon, transfer to <strong>Hoa Lu</strong>, the ancient capital of Vietnam for 41 years under the Dinh and Le dynasty (968AD &ndash; 1009AD) and visit two temples that are dedicated to the <strong>Dinh and Le Kings.</strong><br />\r\nReturn to Hanoi by 18.00&nbsp;<br />\r\nOvernight in Hanoi.</p>\r\n', null, 'b393d1efc5f16ae7fb1f0117d59ee2d1.jpg', '2018-05-31 09:18:20', '2017-11-14 19:33:45', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('392', '78', '8', 'Halong – Hanoi - Fly to Siem Reap (B/L/D)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">You are advised to get up early to enjoy the fresh air and sunrise in the beautiful scenery of <strong>Bai Tu Long</strong>.<br />\r\nBreakfast on the boat.<br />\r\n08:30 - Enjoy activities. Either <strong>visit the cave</strong> or embark a<strong> small bamboo sampan</strong> to visit Vung Vieng Fishing village, one of the spectacular floating villages in Halong. Encounter the locals and fishermen&rsquo;s farm as well as a floating school (depends on the boat&rsquo;s activity schedule)<br />\r\n09:30 - Return to the boat and check out of the cabin.<br />\r\n10:00 - Cruise back to <strong>Hon Gai port.</strong> On the way back, we will enjoy <strong>lunch on the boat.</strong> Last look at the legendary bay where dragons once descended.<br />\r\n11:45 - Arrive at the pier and transfer back to Hanoi&nbsp;and take <strong>flight to Siem Reap in the late afternoon.</strong><br />\r\nUpon arrival, our local tour guide will welcome you at small charming Siem Reap international airport and transfer a short distance to the down town. Check in your hotel and enjoy a briefing tour as well as some first information about this beautiful region.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nA<strong> welcome dinner</strong> with<strong> Apsara Dancing </strong>show will be served in the finest restaurant in the city.<br />\r\nOvernight in Siem Reap.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', null, '0f8f0dee6be71cf0ee53781170b88e48.jpg', '2018-05-31 09:19:34', '2017-11-14 19:36:26', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('391', '78', '7', 'Hanoi – Halong (B/L/D)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">08:00 - Meet our driver for a transfer to Halong via <strong>Bac Ninh and Sao D</strong>o. Extensive rice fields as far as your eyes can see will follow you along the way.<br />\r\n12:00 - Embarkation at <strong>Hon Gai port</strong>, relax with a welcome drink.<br />\r\n13:00 &ndash; Enjoy a seafood lunch on the boat while cruising in to the bay through the enchanting landscapes of <strong>Bai Tu Long Bay</strong> ( Small Dragon Bay).<br />\r\n15:30 - Take part in activities according to the boat such as: <strong>visit Thien Canh Son cave, go kayaking</strong>, take a <strong>bamboo sampan ride</strong> to the <strong>Vang Vieng fishing village</strong> or simply just relax on the boat.<br />\r\n18:00 - Return to the boat, shower and take a rest.<br />\r\n19:00 - Enjoy a delicious dinner on the boat.<br />\r\nStay overnight in a private cabin (with air conditioner and shower)</p>\r\n', null, '61645b3d8968ff67180fc9d54544a087.jpg', '2018-05-31 09:18:56', '2017-11-14 19:34:49', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('393', '78', '9', 'Siem Reap – Angkor Thom – Taprohm – Angkor Wat (B/L/-) ', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">After breakfast at your hotel, meet our tour guide and enjoy a full day discovering the <strong>mysterious Angkor complex temples</strong>, starting from the <strong>South Gate of Angkor Thom</strong>, known as Big Angkor, the last capital of Angkor Empire surrounded by a wall and moat.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Bayon temple</strong> is in the heart of Angkor Thom. It is a special architecture with 54 towers and 4 smiling face statues. All are impressive bas-relief.&nbsp;<br />\r\nOur guide will lead you to the <strong>Terrace of Elephant</strong>. This is a terrace wall adorned with carved elephants Followed by <strong>Baphuon</strong> &ndash; a huge temple mountain and <strong>Terrace of the Leper King</strong> &ndash; a double wall carved with many mythological beings.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTraveling out of <strong>Angkor Thom</strong> and through the jungle will lead us to the sacred <strong>Ta Prohm temple</strong> ruin which is a great combination between human genius and natural beauty. Admire giant trees which have grown here for centuries. This is also the place where the &ldquo;Tomb Raider&rdquo; was filmed.<br />\r\nLunch will be served in the restaurant by the Srah Srang Lake.<br />\r\nIn the afternoon, discover<strong> Angkor Wat temple</strong>, the largest Khmer temple and the finest example of architecture and Angkorian art.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nEnjoy the <strong>sunset</strong> from the <strong>Phnom Bakeng</strong> hill before returning to your hotel for dinner and relaxation.<br />\r\nStay overnight in Siem Reap.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', null, 'a6a6f4c2a84b6f7ef89680e8995ab088.jpg', '2018-05-31 09:20:15', '2017-11-14 19:37:43', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('394', '78', '10', 'Siem Reap – Rolous Group – Banteay Srei (B/L/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Meet our tour guide and driver at your hotel and enjoy a trip to <strong>Rolous Group</strong>. This is the ancient capital of King Indravarman I during 877AD &ndash; 889AD, also known as the birth place of the classical Khmer art and Architecture.<br />\r\nAmong the <strong>Roluos Group temples</strong>, there are some of the earliest permanent structures built by the Khmer empire, dating from the late 9th century. Some were totally built with bricks, others built with laterite or sandstone.<br />\r\nIn the afternoon, visit<strong> Bantey Srei temple </strong>known as the <strong>Women&rsquo;s citadel </strong>and a cradle of the Angkor&rsquo;s finest stone carving.<br />\r\nThe temple is a masterpiece built with red sandstone.<br />\r\nReturn to Siem Reap and relax<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', null, 'dc07a4e96c761f68dbdc3088944ab76b.jpg', '2018-05-31 09:20:32', '2017-11-14 19:38:39', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('395', '78', '11', 'Siem Reap –Tonle Sap Lake – Departure (B/-/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Transfer to<strong> Tonle Sap Lake</strong>, located 10km from the city center. On arrival, <strong>embark a boat </strong>and discover the largest fresh water lake in Southeast Asia, known as one of the world&rsquo;s most varied and productive ecosystems the region that has always been of central importance for <strong>Cambodia&#39;s food provision.</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nDiscover the beauty of the water landscape and local life on the lake, visit a<strong> floating village</strong> and enjoy the encounters with the locals.<br />\r\nBack to city, check out and<strong> transfer to airport </strong>for your <strong>flight to next destinations or flight home.</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nTour ends.</p>\r\n', null, '39bef9b923bfaad8ca00dd70615a791d.jpg', '2018-05-31 09:20:57', '2017-11-14 19:39:29', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('396', '79', '1', 'Saigon arrival (-/-/D)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Upon arrival, meet our Authentik Travel&rsquo;s tour guide and <strong>transfer to hotel in the downtown.</strong><br />\r\nCheck in and relax.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Enjoy our welcome dinner in a finest restaurant </strong>in the city center.<br />\r\nOvernight in Saigon.</p>\r\n', null, '087f22778bebb724fb205cbf30e65a32.jpg', '2018-05-31 09:06:44', '2017-11-14 19:02:30', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('397', '79', '2', 'Saigon Cu chi – full day tour (B/-/-)', '<p>Depart Saigon to discover one of the most striking places in the history of the Vietnam War<strong>,</strong> the <strong>Cu Chi Tunnels.&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Cu Chi is a<strong> real underground city </strong>made up of a large network of tunnels covering an area of over <strong>250km</strong> where the Viet Cong conducted the war of resistance against American troops. All of the tunnels were dug by the Viet Cong over a period of twenty years using only pickaxes and shovels. You will also have a chance to visit <strong>Ben Duoc memorial temple</strong> nearby but far less touristic built in 1993 in memory of the Vietnamese killed at Cu Chi.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nReturn to Saigon.<br />\r\nVisit the <strong>Reunification palace</strong> (or the war memorials Museum), <strong>Notre Dame Cathedral</strong> and the <strong>Central Post Office</strong> inspired by Orsay Station in Paris.<br />\r\nThen, transfer to <strong>Cho Lon District </strong>to discover its <strong>old quarter</strong>, <strong>Binh Tay Market</strong> and the <strong>colorful Quan Am pagoda</strong>, one of the oldest pagodas in the city. Its architecture and decorations have remained since its construction. Overnight in Saigon.</p>\r\n', null, 'd266fa10d24d7f68dfbb674ac6947274.jpg', '2018-05-31 09:07:06', '2017-11-14 19:03:37', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('398', '79', '3', 'Saigon – Ben Tre – Saigon (B/L/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Our&nbsp;tour guide and driver welcome you at your hotel for your transfer to <strong>Ben Tre,</strong> a beautiful region &nbsp;in the Mekong Delta River, famous for making coconut candy.<br />\r\nArrive at<strong> Hung Vuong pier</strong>, then take a boat trip on the Ben Tre River to discover the daily local life.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nStop to visit the<strong> brick kiln of Mr Tu Lo </strong>and discover the craft methods of making bricks.<br />\r\nNext, visit the <strong>coconut factory</strong> and meet Mr Vo Van Ba. He is a man passionate about traditional music and has spent all his life making a collection of fifty folk instruments. Here, you can attend a show to appreciate his passion.<br />\r\nContinue your boat trip on a canal to <strong>Nhon Thanh Village</strong>. This will be an opportunity to<strong> taste the fresh fruits.</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nTake a <strong>bike ride </strong>(or Tuk tuk) on a small path through the villages and enjoy views of the coconut ranges, rice fields and vegetable gardens. A lunch of <strong>Elephant&nbsp;ear&nbsp;fish</strong> is served in the village . A short walk will help you to discover the local life in depth. This is followed by a boat ride on the small canal shaded by the wild palm trees.<br />\r\nFREE OPTION:<br />\r\nFor those who wish to ride a bike, you can go to Mr Sau Khanh&rsquo;s house to admire his collection of ancient objects. Then, continue through the rice fields and meet the locals and join them in their work.<br />\r\nTransfer back to Saigon in the late afternoon.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', null, 'bfee5513c581bd77d3baa7aeddee9d37.jpg', '2018-06-27 04:38:42', '2017-11-14 19:04:42', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('399', '79', '4', 'Saigon – Fly to Danang – Hoian ancient town (B/-/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">After breakfast at your hotel, <strong>transfer to airport </strong>for your short <strong>flight to Danang.</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nMeet our tour guide and driver from&nbsp;Danang airport for 30km coastline to&nbsp;<strong>Hoian ancient town</strong> which is listed in the Heritage of Humans.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nSome real treasures that need to be discovered are <strong>Hoian Museum, Japanese bridge, China Town, Quan Thang ancient house</strong>, the <strong>local market </strong>and the <strong>old busy port</strong> of the 15th century for the international boats from China, Netherlands, Japan, and Poland.<br />\r\nFinally, visit the Thang Loi&nbsp;<strong>silk factory</strong>, known as a good establishment in Hoian to have tailor-made silk clothes.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn the evening,&nbsp;Embark on a <strong>small boat in Hoian town</strong> then depart to <strong>Thu Bon River</strong> which was once a very busy exchange place for a lot of international ships throughout the 15th century. The boat trip will take you along the river to <strong>Cua Dai sea gate</strong>. This is a good chance for you to appreciate the landscape of the peaceful village by the river bank and admire the fishermen&rsquo;s activities on the river. Enjoy the<strong> sunset</strong> in the late afternoon from April to November.<br />\r\nOvernight at Hoian.</p>\r\n', null, '92bc7b70bb246f1958d80295add3135c.jpg', '2018-05-31 09:07:57', '2017-11-14 19:05:41', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('400', '79', '5', 'Hoian – Tra Que – Cam Thanh (B/L/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">At 8:00am, go on a <strong>bike ride</strong> (or car) to <strong>Tra Que farming village</strong>. It is famous for its aromatic herbs, mint and basil. Their leaves are smaller than normal ones and have a special flavor.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nBike through the village and <strong>vegetable fields</strong> and meet the farmers who work all the seasons of the year. It is a good opportunity to observe the techniques of vegetable gardening.<br />\r\nEnjoy crab catching in the water palm trees forest. This is a relaxing moment after hours of biking.<br />\r\nContinue biking to <strong>Cam Thanh</strong>. Along the way the landscapes of fishing farms and water palm trees will accompany you. Arrive in Cam Thanh and embark a small round bamboo <strong>sampan basket boat&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\nLunch is served in family restaurant Mr Day, a family fisherman working in tourism.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAfter lunch, enjoy a nice walk in the village to discover how they make <strong>nipa for roofs</strong> and their daily activities.<br />\r\nOvernight in Hoian.</p>\r\n', null, 'd2b188ba717a61d94d08f7a5182a560d.jpg', '2018-05-31 09:09:12', '2017-11-14 19:09:00', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('401', '79', '6', 'Hoian – My Son – Transfer to Hue (B/-/-)', '<p>Have breakfast at your hotel and depart to the sacred valley of the <strong>Champa Kingdom</strong>. Located 70km from Hoian Town, <strong>My Son</strong> was the capital of the Champa Kingdom which ruled central Vietnam between the 4th and 13th century AD.<br />\r\nRecognized as a <strong>World Culture Heritage</strong> site by Unesco, the site preserves the 70 ruined architecture works of bricks and stones built between the 7th and 13th century</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Return to Hoian at 13.00 for a <strong>transfer to Hue</strong>. Drive along the coastline and arrive in <strong>Danang.</strong> Enjoy a walk to <strong>My Khe beach</strong> where you can enjoy the view of giant <strong>Goodness of Mercy</strong> statues in the <strong>Linh Ung Pagoda</strong>. Take photos of fishermen by the beach and visit the <strong>Cham Museum </strong>which preserves the most important <strong>Cham culture </strong>collections in the world.<br />\r\nContinue to Hue on the Mandarin Road via <strong>Sea Cloud Pass</strong> (Hai Van Pass). Stop on the top of the pass to enjoy the breathtaking view to the ocean and Da Nang city.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nArrive in Hue &ndash; check in your hotel.</p>\r\n', null, 'c9f06e1fcbd890c75f6a53297abba0ac.jpg', '2018-05-31 09:09:44', '2017-11-14 19:10:07', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('402', '79', '7', 'Hue City tour (B/-/-)', '<p>At 8.00, transfer upstream of the <strong>Perfume river</strong> to visit the emperor,<strong> Minh Mang&#39;s tomb</strong>, an architectural masterpiece that harmoniously highlights the nature and imperial religious works.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAfter that, we will voyage along the Perfume River to <strong>Thuy Bieu Village</strong> taking in the picturesque landscapes on both sides. After 1 hour, we arrive in Thuy Bieu known for its divine grapefruit trees where you can take a bike around the village under the shade of the grapefruit trees and enjoy their pleasant perfume aroma and the harvested straw. The peaceful atmosphere is in every corner of the village.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThen, <strong>visit a temple</strong> dedicated to the village protector, a traditional garden house built several centuries ago. This is a wonderful opportunity to stop for great photos and interact with the villagers working in the gardens and vegetable fields which should not be missed.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Lunch is served at Mrs. Loan</strong> in the village of Thuy Bieu.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the afternoon, visit <strong>Thien Mu Pagoda,</strong> &nbsp;one of the oldest pagodas in Hue, dating back to 1601. This is the spiritual highlight of the city and well known for its majestic octagon tower and beautiful view of the <strong>Perfume River.</strong><br />\r\nThen, continue to the most anticipated site in Hue, <strong>Hue citadel</strong>, the only vestige symbol for what was once the imperial city of Vietnam. It is inspired by the fortification of Vauban. The city is composed of three parts: Kinh Thanh (<strong>the Capital city</strong>), Hoang Thanh (<strong>the Imperial city</strong>) and Cam Thanh (<strong>the Forbidden City</strong>).The most beautiful sites in Hue are concentrated in this area including the <strong>flag tower, the South gate, the palace of supreme Harmony</strong>, the Dynasty temple area and the settlement area. During the visit, we will attend a <strong>traditional dancing show</strong> in the royal theater.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nReturn to your hotel.<br />\r\nOvernight in Hue.</p>\r\n', null, 'be361b09a2a85fd9d30ec777768c4593.jpg', '2018-05-31 09:10:21', '2017-11-14 19:12:19', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('403', '79', '8', 'Hue – Fly to Hanoi – city tour (B/-/-)', '<p>Transfer to Hue airport <strong>for a morning&nbsp;flight to Hanoi.</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nOn arrival, get a pick up to the city center. Leave your luggage at hotel and <strong>enjoy a full day city tour.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Today, we discover the wonders of the <strong>capital of Vietnam</strong>, filled with timeless charm. Start by visiting <strong>Van Mieu (Temple of Literature)</strong>, the first University of Vietnam built from the 11th century by Emperor Ly Thanh Tong.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAfter that, transfer to the<strong> Ethnology Museum</strong> (closed every Monday) which offers a deep insight into Vietnamese culture through traditional costumes, tools, musical instruments and traditional houses of many minority ethnic groups.<br />\r\n<strong>Lunch </strong>is served in a local restaurant.<br />\r\nIn the afternoon, discover the <strong>Ho Chi Minh complex</strong> including the <strong>Presidential Palace, Ho Chi Minh&#39;s House on stilts and the fish pond</strong>.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor those who are interested in visiting the <strong>Ho Chi Minh Mausoleum</strong>, it is only open in the morning and closed every Monday and Friday. Sometimes it is necessary to queue for a couple of hours to go inside the mausoleum.<br />\r\nTransfer to the old quarter to visit Hoan Kiem lake (Restored Sword Lake) and Ngoc Son temple in the middle of the lake.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Return to your hotel in the late afternoon.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nOvernight in Hanoi.</p>\r\n', null, '20a21090177f63a9ca5de3b0729b842f.jpg', '2018-05-31 09:11:41', '2017-11-14 19:16:17', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('404', '79', '9', 'Hanoi – Halong (B/L/D).', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">08:00 - Meet our driver for a transfer to Halong via <strong>Bac Ninh and Sao D</strong>o. Extensive rice fields as far as your eyes can see will follow you along the way.<br />\r\n12:00 - Embarkation at <strong>Hon Gai port</strong>, relax with a welcome drink.<br />\r\n13:00 &ndash; Enjoy a seafood lunch on the boat while cruising in to the bay through the enchanting landscapes of <strong>Bai Tu Long Bay</strong> ( Small Dragon Bay).<br />\r\n15:30 - Take part in activities according to the boat such as: <strong>visit Thien Canh Son cave, go kayaking</strong>, take a <strong>bamboo sampan ride</strong> to the <strong>Vang Vieng fishing village</strong> or simply just relax on the boat.<br />\r\n18:00 - Return to the boat, shower and take a rest.<br />\r\n19:00 - Enjoy a delicious dinner on the boat.<br />\r\nStay overnight in a private cabin (with air conditioner and shower)</p>\r\n', null, 'ff87d64b00ee0a6cd565498bd8b792fd.jpg', '2018-05-31 09:12:04', '2017-11-14 19:17:50', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('405', '79', '10', 'Halong – Hanoi – Fly to Luang Prabang (B/L-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">You are advised to get up early to enjoy the fresh air and sunrise in the beautiful scenery of Bai Tu Long.<br />\r\nBreakfast on the boat.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n08:30 - Enjoy activities. Either <strong>visit the cave</strong> or embark a<strong> small bamboo sampan</strong> to visit Vung Vieng Fishing village, one of the spectacular floating villages in Halong. Encounter the locals and fishermen&rsquo;s farm as well as a floating school (depends on the boat&rsquo;s activity schedule)<br />\r\n09:30 - Return to the boat and check out of the cabin.<br />\r\n10:00 - Cruise back to <strong>Hon Gai port.</strong> On the way back, we will enjoy <strong>lunch on the boat.</strong> Last look at the legendary bay where dragons once descended.<br />\r\n11:45 - Arrive at the pier and transfer back to Hanoi and directly to airport&nbsp;for a short<strong>&nbsp;flight to Luang Prabang.</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nUpon Luang Prabang airport, our local tour guide and driver will <strong>welcome you and transfer to your hote</strong>l in the city center. Meals on your own and take a rest.<br />\r\nOvernight in Luang Prabang.</p>\r\n', null, 'a6ba523584909703fe73781ec772d2ea.jpg', '2018-05-31 09:12:35', '2017-11-14 19:19:31', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('406', '79', '11', 'Luang Prabang – City Tour - Khuang Si fall –full day (B/L/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">After breakfast at your hotel, meet our tour guide and driver to go to <strong>Mount Phousi</strong> where you can enjoy a great panoramic view of the City and the river.<br />\r\nTake a short drive to <strong>Vat Xien Thong</strong> (the temple of Royal city). This is one of the most important Laotian monasteries and still remains a significant monument to the spirit of religion, traditional art and royalty.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe next&nbsp; stop will be <strong>Wat Visoun temple</strong>, dating back to 1513 and the reign of <strong>King Visoun</strong> . This is the oldest temple in Luang Prabang and was once the home to Luang Prabang Buddhas. <strong>Wat Visoun temple </strong>is with an unusual structure which represents the earliest Laotian style.<br />\r\nFollow this with a visit to <strong>Wat Mai</strong>, a beautiful temple built in the 18th century, located by the Royal palace. It is the biggest temple in Luang Prabang with beautiful decorations.<br />\r\nEnjoy a driving through rice fields and a beautiful small village. Make some stops to discover their daily life before reaching<strong> Khuang Si fall,</strong> a gorgeous turquoise waterfall. <strong>Refresh and swim</strong> in the clear water.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nReturn to city and spend the rest of day at your leisure.<br />\r\nStay overnight at a hotel in Luang Prabang.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', null, '8ac822b8b728f299b9ffb4faef4c3f7d.jpg', '2018-05-31 09:13:16', '2017-11-14 19:22:22', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('407', '79', '12', 'Luang Prabang – Pak Ou cave – Local village (B/-/-) full day', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Have breakfast at your hotel then visit a <strong>local market</strong> in the town to discover the daily life. (We recommend visiting early in the morning).<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTransfer to the pier, embark a <strong>boat and enjoy a trip</strong> upstream along the Mekong River. Discover the <strong>numerous Buddha images in the Pak Oo caves </strong>such as <strong>Pak Oo cave</strong> (the mouth of the Oo River), <strong>Tham Ting cave</strong> ( Lower cave) and <strong>Tham Theung</strong> ( Upper cave). They are on the right side and overlook the Mekong River. Travel a short distance from the caves to the village of <strong>Ban Xang Hai</strong>.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nEncounter the locals and learn how to make LauLao (Laotian whisky) and <strong>LauHa</strong>i (Laotian wine). Return to the city, making stops at &nbsp;<strong>Ban Xang Khong village</strong> and <strong>Ban Xieng Lek village</strong>, well known for handmade <strong>Jute Sar paper</strong>.<br />\r\nReturn to your hotel and relax and stay overnight in Luang Prabang.</p>\r\n', null, 'a295fd9c4f9e379407970942be7594be.jpg', '2018-05-31 09:13:47', '2017-11-14 19:23:33', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('408', '79', '13', 'Luang Prabang – Khmu Village – Wat Tham Xieng Maen (B/L/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">In the morning, meet our tour guide at your hotel and you cross the <strong>Mekong River </strong>via a local ferry towards <strong>Khmu village</strong>. En route, make a short visit to <strong>Ban Chan pottery village</strong>. It is a rare chance to try your hand at creating beautiful pots from clay.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAlong the way, you will pass through some <strong>rustic villages</strong>, encounter the local people, and see the children playing together or farmers doing their work on the fields. Visit<strong> Ban Boum Xieng</strong> to observe the ethnic traditions and daily life. Continue driving to a <strong>Khmu family</strong> and enjoy lunch with them.<br />\r\nIn the afternoon, drive back to the Mekong River and discover the decorative, less visited <strong>Wat Long Khun temple</strong>. From here, take a short transfer to <strong>Wat Tham Xieng Maen</strong> located in a limestone cave and visit its Buddha images.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe last highlight of the day is <strong>Wat Chom phet</strong> - This is an excellent spot for a panoramic view of the area as well as an excellent photo opportunity for a <strong>sunset photo hunter.</strong><br />\r\nReturn to your hotel and stay overnight in Luang Prabang.</p>\r\n', null, 'ba101a8d1d8697ddad084eef06f507fe.jpg', '2018-05-31 09:14:38', '2017-11-14 19:24:40', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('409', '79', '14', 'Luang Prabang – Departure (B/-/-)', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Free till meet our driver to<strong> transfer to airport </strong>for your<strong> flight home</strong> or next destination.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTour ends.</p>\r\n', null, '48dc0578dd78810e3d58bab266518ad6.jpg', '2017-11-15 02:24:57', '2017-11-14 19:24:57', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('410', '80', '1', 'Hanoi arrival – walking tour ( 2km) (D)', '<p><strong>Be welcomed</strong> at the airport by our Authentik Travel&#39;s tour guide&nbsp;and<strong> transfer to your hotel</strong> in the city center.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Check in at your hotel (after 12:00pm) or leave your luggage at the hotel and enjoy a<strong> walk in the old quarter</strong>. The city was built in the 10<sup>th</sup> century by the villagers near the <strong>Red River Delta</strong>. You can see the special architecture in the houses with their narrow width and deep length. You will be able to discover some popular streets such as<strong> Ma May, Hang Ma, Hang Dong, Hang Bac and Hang Gai </strong>and for tourist sites stop at <strong>Dong Xuan market,</strong> the biggest market in the northern Vietnam, <strong>Bach Ma temple</strong> (White horse temple) and the <strong>traditional ancient house</strong> at 87 Ma May Street. Head back to your hotel.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nEnjoy our <strong>welcome dinner </strong>at a finest local restaurant and overnight in Hanoi.</p>\r\n', null, '2b4faebe75a8dd789f6b8fd979a36a5d.jpg', '2018-05-31 08:49:23', '2017-11-14 04:07:12', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('411', '80', '2', 'Hanoi – City Tour – Train to Sapa (B/L/)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Today, we discover the wonders of the <strong>capital of Vietnam</strong>, filled with timeless charm. Start by visiting <strong>Van Mieu (Temple of Literature)</strong>, the first University of Vietnam built from the 11th century by Emperor Ly Thanh Tong. Continue to visit <strong>Chua Ha (Ha Pagoda)</strong>, known as a sacred place to pray for luck in love, especially for your future spouse.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAfter that, transfer to the<strong> Ethnology Museum</strong> (closed every Monday) which offers a deep insight into Vietnamese culture through traditional costumes, tools, musical instruments and traditional houses of many minority ethnic groups. Enjoy a special<strong> water puppet show in the museum garden.</strong><br />\r\n<strong>Lunch </strong>is served in a local restaurant.<br />\r\nIn the afternoon, discover the <strong>Ho Chi Minh complex</strong> including the <strong>Presidential Palace, Ho Chi Minh&#39;s House on stilts and the fish pond</strong>.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor those who are interested in visiting the <strong>Ho Chi Minh Mausoleum</strong>, it is only open in the morning and closed every Monday and Friday. Sometimes it is necessary to queue for a couple of hours to go inside the mausoleum.<br />\r\nTransfer to the old quarter to visit Hoan Kiem lake (Restored Sword Lake) and Ngoc Son temple in the middle of the lake. In the late afternoon, take a night train to Sapa.<br />\r\nOvernight on Train (Share 4 Berth AC cabin).</p>\r\n', null, '492cd48c6db85a23514d4ac0a180df9d.jpg', '2018-05-31 08:49:43', '2017-11-14 04:09:12', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('412', '80', '3', 'Sapa – Cat Cat – Y Linh Ho – Lao Chai – Ta Van (B/L/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Arrive in Lao Cai</strong>&nbsp;in the early morning, our local guide will pick you up at the railway station and&nbsp;<strong>transfer to Sapa town.&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nEnjoy breakfast at local restaurant and&nbsp;start a full day of <strong>trekking from Cat Cat Village</strong> of the Black Hmong. Visit its beautiful<strong> waterfall</strong> then follow the path to <strong>Y Linh Ho village.</strong><br />\r\nArrive at<strong> Y Linh Ho bridge</strong>. Stop to relax a little bit then resume trekking along the <strong>buffalo path</strong> through the hills. You will have chance to enjoy the splendid view over the<strong> rice terrace valley</strong> considered one of the most fantastic of the world.<br />\r\nLunch will be served on the way.<br />\r\nAfter lunch take a short break before trekking to the<strong> Lao Chai village </strong>of the black Hmong and <strong>Ta Van village</strong> of the Zay people.<br />\r\nAt 16.00 meet our driver and transfer to Sapa<br />\r\nOvernight in Sapa.</p>\r\n', null, '1bbfb7f2066095e79a513034c96969be.jpg', '2018-05-31 08:50:03', '2017-11-14 04:10:11', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('413', '80', '4', 'Sapa Discovery – Night train to Hanoi (B/-/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">After breakfast at your hotel, our guide will meet you for a visit to&nbsp;<strong>Silver Water fall.</strong>&nbsp;This is one of the highest and most beautiful falls in Sapa.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTransfer further 3 km to reach&nbsp;<strong>Tram Ton Pass &ndash; 2000m from the sea level.&nbsp;</strong>You will feel the drop of temperature but the views are so gorgeous.<br />\r\nIt time for you to relax and take photos before driving back to Sapa town for your own lunch, relax then checkout the hotel before exploring the<strong>&nbsp;Dragon Jaw Mountain.</strong>&nbsp;Walking up to the mountain is the way to enjoy the beauty of the landscapes and alot of flowers on the way.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFrom the top of the&nbsp;<strong>Dragon Jaw Mountain</strong>, you will able to view all charming Sapa town&nbsp;and the&nbsp;<strong>Peak of Fansipan from distance.</strong><br />\r\nDinner is on your own then transfer to&nbsp;<strong>Lao Cai railway station for night train to Hanoi.</strong><br />\r\nOvernight on train ( Share 4 berth AC cabin).</p>\r\n', null, '52905cd70885e6c206185f2b3fa6420d.jpg', '2018-05-31 08:50:23', '2017-11-14 04:11:20', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('414', '80', '5', 'Hanoi – Halong Bay (B/L/D)', '<p>Arrival in Hanoi in the early morning, check in a hotel by the railway station for your refreshment and breakfast.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>08:00 - Meet our driver for a transfer to Halong via <strong>Bac Ninh and Sao D</strong>o. Extensive rice fields as far as your eyes can see will follow you along the way.<br />\r\n12:00 - Embarkation at <strong>Hon Gai port</strong>, relax with a welcome drink.<br />\r\n13:00 &ndash; Enjoy a seafood lunch on the boat while cruising in to the bay through the enchanting landscapes of <strong>Bai Tu Long Bay</strong> ( Small Dragon Bay).<br />\r\n15:30 - Take part in activities according to the boat such as: <strong>visit Thien Canh Son cave, go kayaking</strong>, take a <strong>bamboo sampan ride</strong> to the <strong>Vang Vieng fishing village</strong> or simply just relax on the boat.<br />\r\n18:00 - Return to the boat, shower and take a rest.<br />\r\n19:00 - Enjoy a delicious dinner on the boat.<br />\r\nStay overnight in a private cabin (with air conditioner and shower)</p>\r\n', null, '1ca4bdbd91f481eb2e5d523093a6458b.jpg', '2018-05-31 08:50:47', '2017-11-14 04:11:57', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('415', '80', '6', 'Halong – Hanoi – fly to Danang - Hoian (B/L/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">You are advised to get up early to enjoy the fresh air and sunrise in the beautiful scenery of Bai Tu Long.<br />\r\nBreakfast on the boat.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n08:30 - Enjoy activities. Either <strong>visit the cave</strong> or embark a<strong> small bamboo sampan</strong> to visit Vung Vieng Fishing village, one of the spectacular floating villages in Halong. Encounter the locals and fishermen&rsquo;s farm as well as a floating school (depends on the boat&rsquo;s activity schedule)<br />\r\n09:30 - Return to the boat and check out of the cabin.<br />\r\n10:00 - Cruise back to <strong>Hon Gai port.</strong> On the way back, we will enjoy <strong>lunch on the boat.</strong> Last look at the legendary bay where dragons once descended.<br />\r\n11:45 - Arrive at the pier and transfer back to Hanoi&nbsp;and directly to airport for a <strong>short flight to Danang city.</strong><br />\r\nOn arrival, pick up and <strong>transfer to Hoian ancient town</strong>.<br />\r\nNote: Cruise&rsquo;s activities order will be depend on each cruises and tide. It is adjustable.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nOvernight in Hoian.</p>\r\n', null, '0f8f0dee6be71cf0ee53781170b88e48.jpg', '2018-05-31 08:51:26', '2017-11-14 19:40:19', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('416', '80', '7', 'Hoian Tour (B/-/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Enjoy a city tour in <strong>Hoian ancient town</strong> which is listed in the Heritage of Humans.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nSome real treasures that need to be discovered are <strong>Hoian Museum, Japanese bridge, China Town, Quan Thang ancient house</strong>, the <strong>local market </strong>and the <strong>old busy port</strong> of the 15th century for the international boats from China, Netherlands, Japan, and Poland.<br />\r\nFinally, visit the Thang Loi&nbsp;<strong>silk factory</strong>, known as a good establishment in Hoian to have tailor-made silk clothes.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn the evening,&nbsp;Embark on a <strong>small boat in Hoian town</strong> then depart to <strong>Thu Bon River</strong> which was once a very busy exchange place for a lot of international ships throughout the 15th century. The boat trip will take you along the river to <strong>Cua Dai sea gate</strong>. This is a good chance for you to appreciate the landscape of the peaceful village by the river bank and admire the fishermen&rsquo;s activities on the river. Enjoy the sunset in the late afternoon from April to November.<br />\r\nOvernight at Hoian.</p>\r\n', null, '994e9bcc1463d713d5be3a7f8a40f3af.jpg', '2018-05-31 08:51:45', '2017-11-14 04:13:52', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('417', '80', '8', 'Hoian – Danang – fly to Ho Chi Minh city ( Saigon) (B/-/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Transfer to Danang airport and take a <strong>morning flight to Saigon.</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nOn arrival, Meet our tour guide and driver and transfer to your hotel. Leave you luggage and enjoy a full day city tour.<br />\r\nVisit the <strong>Reunification palace</strong> (or the war memorials Museum), <strong>Notre Dame Cathedral</strong> and the <strong>Central Post Office</strong> inspired by Orsay Station in Paris.<br />\r\nThen, transfer to <strong>Cho Lon District </strong>to discover its <strong>old quarter</strong>, <strong>Binh Tay Market</strong> and the <strong>colorful Quan Am pagoda</strong>, one of the oldest pagodas in the city. Its architecture and decorations have remained since its construction.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nReturn to Saigon city for a <strong>walk in the city center</strong> visiting sites like the former<strong> Catinat streets</strong>, the <strong>Opera house</strong>, <strong>City Hall</strong> as well as <strong>Ben Thanh market.</strong><br />\r\nOvernight in Saigon.</p>\r\n', null, '17fd68242d45fa00c47d337802cd2a94.jpg', '2018-05-31 08:52:07', '2017-11-14 04:15:48', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('420', '80', '10', 'Can Tho – Chau Doc (B/-/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Have breakfast at the hotel and<strong> transfer to the pier</strong> for a <strong>boat trip to visit Cai Rang floating market</strong>, the largest and most lively market in the Mekong Delta.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThere are so many colors and smells in the bubbling atmosphere where hundreds of sampans are filled with goods such as rice, fruits, and craft products. Everything is shown to sell from the early morning.<br />\r\nLeave the market and continue the<strong> boat trip through the canals</strong> and visit a fruit garden (Option - replace the garden with the nursery field by the river)<br />\r\nHead back to <strong>An Binh Market</strong> which is full of fish, fruits and vegetables.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nStop at <strong>Binh Thuy ancient house</strong> which contains the orchid garden where &ldquo;The Lover&rdquo; was filmed.<br />\r\n<strong>Transfer to Chau Doc.</strong><br />\r\nOn arrival, check in hotel and enjoy a walking the town as well as a visit to <strong>Sam mountain</strong> with colorful temples and Pagodas: <strong>Xu Lady Pagoda, Thoai Ngoc Hau temple, Tay An pagoda.</strong><br />\r\n<strong>Enjoy the sunset</strong> over the border between Vietnam and Cambodia.<br />\r\nOvernight in Chau Doc.</p>\r\n', null, '33ab39b2c8aeae4826bf0128f7d88cde.jpg', '2018-05-31 08:53:00', '2017-11-14 04:17:48', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('421', '80', '11', 'Chau Doc – High speed boat to Phnom Penh (B/-/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">In the morning, transfer to pier to take high speed boat at 7.00am to <strong>PhnomPenh</strong><br />\r\nUpon arrival, local tour guide will pick you up to your hotel in the city center. Check in your hotel and enjoy a briefing tour as well as some first information about this beautiful region.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nStart with a visit to the <strong>impressive colorful Khmer-style royal palace</strong> complex built in 1866 by the Predecessors of King Norodom. Nearby is <strong>Silver pagoda </strong>(the emerald Buddha temple), which contains plenty of decorated Buddha Statues made of gold, diamond, gemstones and silver. Then visit the <strong>National Museum.</strong><br />\r\nOvernight in Phnom Penh.</p>\r\n', null, '21fee21c2223bd126b9d1f9a03eeb82a.jpg', '2018-05-31 08:54:04', '2017-11-14 04:18:46', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('419', '80', '9', 'Saigon – Cai Be – Can Tho (B/L/-) ', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Get picked up from your hotel and transfer to <strong>Cai Be</strong> ( 120km &ndash; 2.5 hour driving). Visit <strong>Cao Dai temple</strong> on route.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nUpon arrival, embark on a <strong>boat trip </strong>on a branch of the Mekong River to Vinh Long. Experience the rhythm of life on the l<strong>egendary Mekong River </strong>with a visit to <strong>Cai Be floating market </strong>and the <strong>orchid canals </strong>.<br />\r\nVisit crafts <strong>workshops </strong>of rice<strong>,</strong> popcorn, coconut caramel and rice cake.<br />\r\n<strong>Cycle or walk </strong>on the <strong>village paths</strong> to discover the ancient and beautiful <strong>Phu Chau pagoda</strong> where serenity reigns and meet the local people.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Enjoy &nbsp;lunch</strong> in an open air restaurant where you can taste a famous local specialty, the<strong> Elephant ear fish.</strong> Then enjoy <strong>tasting delicious fruits</strong> while rowing a <strong>small rowboat</strong> in the canals shaded by the fruit trees.<br />\r\nContinue your boat trip to <strong>Vinh Long</strong> and meet our driver at the pier for a<strong> transfer to Can Tho</strong>. Arrive in Can Tho in the late afternoon. &nbsp;Check in at your hotel and relax.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nEnjoy free time on your own to discover the city located on the Mekong River.<br />\r\nStay overnight in Can Tho.</p>\r\n', null, '5a1751ab1fd7a80c76df4d6432ddb9c6.jpg', '2018-06-27 04:37:58', '2017-11-14 04:16:38', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('422', '80', '12', 'Phnom Penh city tour (B/-/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Have breakfast at your hotel, then spend a full day learning about the <strong>Khmer rouge</strong> in the past and Cambodia in the present.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn the morning, start to visit&nbsp;<strong>Choeung Ek museum</strong> or the<strong> Killing fields</strong>, where about 17 000 innocent Cambodian people (during1975 and 1978) including men, women, children and infants were detained and tortured at S-21 prison then transported for their extermination.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe continue to <strong>Tuol Sleng prison</strong>, now the <strong>Genocide Museum</strong>, the most secret part of the Khmer Rouge regime. It&rsquo;s also called<strong> S-21</strong> (abbreviated for Security Office 21), Khmer Rouge&#39;s premier security camp, specifically designed for the interrogation and extermination of anti-Angkor elements.<br />\r\nIt&#39;s surprising to know that S-21 used to be a high school before becoming this awful place during Khmer Rouge regime.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nReturn to the city to discover the local daily life at the <strong>Russian market</strong> and enjoy the bustling daily activities of the locals.&nbsp;<br />\r\nGo back to your hotel and relax.<br />\r\nNote: Please consider a different trip to the killing fields and S2-1 prison if you have small children in the group. We will offer other suitable alternative programs such as <strong>Koh Dach Island or Tamao wildlife </strong>rescue center.</p>\r\n', null, 'db3751e6ce1bc62dc9ca946e40a4076c.jpg', '2018-05-31 08:54:38', '2017-11-14 04:19:33', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('423', '80', '13', 'Phnom Penh – Fly to Siem Reap – Rolous group – Banteay Srei (B/-/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Tranfer to airport for <strong>flight to Siem Reap</strong>. Upon arrival, get a pick up and <strong>transfer to hotel.</strong> Check in your hotel and enjoy a briefing tour as well as some first information about this beautiful region.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nEnjoy a trip to <strong>Rolous Group</strong>. This is the ancient capital of King Indravarman I during 877AD &ndash; 889AD, also known as the birth place of the classical Khmer art and Architecture.<br />\r\nAmong the <strong>Roluos Group temples</strong>, there are some of the earliest permanent structures built by the Khmer empire, dating from the late 9th century. Some were totally built with bricks, others built with laterite or sandstone.<br />\r\nIn the afternoon, visit<strong> Bantey Srei temple </strong>known as the <strong>Women&rsquo;s citadel </strong>and a cradle of the Angkor&rsquo;s finest stone carving.<br />\r\nThe temple is a masterpiece built with red sandstone.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Return to Siem Reap and relax.<br />\r\nOvernight in Siem Reap.</p>\r\n', null, '88360d6bd05efff5befecc9acf8d8a11.jpg', '2018-05-31 08:55:33', '2017-11-14 04:20:29', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('424', '80', '14', 'Siem Reap – Angkor Thom – Taprohm – Angkor Wat (B/L/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">After breakfast at your hotel, meet our tour guide and enjoy a full day discovering the <strong>mysterious Angkor complex temples</strong>, starting from the <strong>South Gate of Angkor Thom</strong>, known as Big Angkor, the last capital of Angkor Empire surrounded by a wall and moat.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Bayon temple</strong> is in the heart of Angkor Thom. It is a special architecture with 54 towers and 4 smiling face statues. All are impressive bas-relief.&nbsp;<br />\r\nOur guide will lead you to the <strong>Terrace of Elephant</strong>. This is a terrace wall adorned with carved elephants Followed by <strong>Baphuon</strong> &ndash; a huge temple mountain and <strong>Terrace of the Leper King</strong> &ndash; a double wall carved with many mythological beings.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTraveling out of <strong>Angkor Thom</strong> and through the jungle will lead us to the sacred <strong>Ta Prohm temple</strong> ruin which is a great combination between human genius and natural beauty. Admire giant trees which have grown here for centuries. This is also the place where the &ldquo;Tomb Raider&rdquo; was filmed.<br />\r\nLunch will be served in the restaurant by the Srah Srang Lake.<br />\r\nIn the afternoon, discover<strong> Angkor Wat temple</strong>, the largest Khmer temple and the finest example of architecture and Angkorian art.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nEnjoy the <strong>sunset</strong> from the <strong>Phnom Bakeng</strong> hill before returning to your hotel for dinner and relaxation.<br />\r\nStay overnight in Siem Reap.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', null, '21fb04b285cc90fa862a0fd2faf6bdb0.jpg', '2018-05-31 08:56:11', '2017-11-14 04:21:18', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('425', '80', '15', 'Siem Reap – floating Village – Departure (B/-/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Transfer to<strong> Tonle Sap Lake</strong>, located 10km from the city center. On arrival, <strong>embark a boat </strong>and discover the largest fresh water lake in Southeast Asia, known as one of the world&rsquo;s most varied and productive ecosystems the region that has always been of central importance for <strong>Cambodia&#39;s food provision.</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nDiscover the beauty of the water landscape and local life on the lake, visit a<strong> floating village</strong> and enjoy the encounters with the locals.<br />\r\nBack to city, check out and<strong> transfer to airport</strong> for your <strong>flight to next destinations</strong> or flight home.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTour ends.</p>\r\n', null, '13779a2bb9304195e29c509cd83aea66.jpg', '2018-05-31 08:56:31', '2017-11-14 04:22:07', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('426', '81', '1', 'Hanoi arrival – walking tour ( 2km) (D)', '<p><strong>Be welcomed</strong> at the airport by our Authentik Travel&#39;s tour guide&nbsp;and<strong> transfer to your hotel</strong> in the city center.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Check in at your hotel (after 12:00pm) or leave your luggage at the hotel and enjoy a<strong> walk in the old quarter</strong>. The city was built in the 10<sup>th</sup> century by the villagers near the <strong>Red River Delta</strong>. You can see the special architecture in the houses with their narrow width and deep length. You will be able to discover some popular streets such as<strong> Ma May, Hang Ma, Hang Dong, Hang Bac and Hang Gai </strong>and for tourist sites stop at <strong>Dong Xuan market,</strong> the biggest market in the northern Vietnam, <strong>Bach Ma temple</strong> (White horse temple) and the <strong>traditional ancient house</strong> at 87 Ma May Street. Head back to your hotel.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nEnjoy our <strong>welcome dinner </strong>at a finest local restaurant and overnight in Hanoi.</p>\r\n', null, '262562cb8d581d42fb176f1f8dfe826a.jpg', '2018-05-31 08:25:36', '2017-11-14 03:19:58', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('427', '81', '2', 'Hanoi – City Tour – Train to Sapa (B/L/)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Today, we discover the wonders of the <strong>capital of Vietnam</strong>, filled with timeless charm. Start by visiting <strong>Van Mieu (Temple of Literature)</strong>, the first University of Vietnam built from the 11th century by Emperor Ly Thanh Tong. Continue to visit <strong>Chua Ha (Ha Pagoda)</strong>, known as a sacred place to pray for luck in love, especially for your future spouse.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAfter that, transfer to the<strong> Ethnology Museum</strong> (closed every Monday) which offers a deep insight into Vietnamese culture through traditional costumes, tools, musical instruments and traditional houses of many minority ethnic groups. Enjoy a special<strong> water puppet show in the museum garden.</strong><br />\r\n<strong>Lunch </strong>is served in a local restaurant.<br />\r\nIn the afternoon, discover the <strong>Ho Chi Minh complex</strong> including the <strong>Presidential Palace, Ho Chi Minh&#39;s House on stilts and the fish pond</strong>.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor those who are interested in visiting the <strong>Ho Chi Minh Mausoleum</strong>, it is only open in the morning and closed every Monday and Friday. Sometimes it is necessary to queue for a couple of hours to go inside the mausoleum.<br />\r\nTransfer to the old quarter to visit Hoan Kiem lake (Restored Sword Lake) and Ngoc Son temple in the middle of the lake. In the late afternoon, take a night train to Sapa.<br />\r\nOvernight on Train (Share 4 Berth AC cabin).</p>\r\n', null, '588bc91503877818b47d3dcbf8d06103.jpg', '2018-05-31 08:25:58', '2017-11-14 03:27:27', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('428', '81', '3', 'Sapa – Cat Cat – Y Linh Ho – Lao Chai – Ta Van (B/L/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Arrive in Lao Cai</strong>&nbsp;in the early morning, our local guide will pick you up at the railway station and&nbsp;<strong>transfer to Sapa town.&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nEnjoy breakfast at local restaurant and&nbsp;start a full day of <strong>trekking from Cat Cat Village</strong> of the Black Hmong. Visit its beautiful<strong> waterfall</strong> then follow the path to <strong>Y Linh Ho village.</strong><br />\r\nArrive at<strong> Y Linh Ho bridge</strong>. Stop to relax a little bit then resume trekking along the <strong>buffalo path</strong> through the hills. You will have chance to enjoy the splendid view over the<strong> rice terrace valley</strong> considered one of the most fantastic of the world.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nLunch will be served on the way.<br />\r\nAfter lunch take a short break before trekking to the<strong> Lao Chai village </strong>of the black Hmong and <strong>Ta Van village</strong> of the Zay people.<br />\r\nAt 16.00 meet our driver and transfer to Sapa<br />\r\nOvernight in Sapa.</p>\r\n', null, '08a5acd9a7b899fe28f42f9ac9b3403e.jpg', '2018-05-31 08:26:28', '2017-11-14 03:29:58', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('429', '81', '4', 'Sapa Discovery – Night train to Hanoi (B/-/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">After breakfast at your hotel, our guide will meet you for a visit to&nbsp;<strong>Silver Water fall.</strong>&nbsp;This is one of the highest and most beautiful falls in Sapa.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTransfer further 3 km to reach&nbsp;<strong>Tram Ton Pass &ndash; 2000m from the sea level.&nbsp;</strong>You will feel the drop of temperature but the views are so gorgeous.<br />\r\nIt time for you to relax and take photos before driving back to Sapa town for your own lunch, relax then checkout the hotel before exploring the<strong>&nbsp;Dragon Jaw Mountain.</strong>&nbsp;Walking up to the mountain is the way to enjoy the beauty of the landscapes and alot of flowers on the way.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFrom the top of the&nbsp;<strong>Dragon Jaw Mountain</strong>, you will able to view all charming Sapa town&nbsp;and the&nbsp;<strong>Peak of Fansipan from distance.</strong><br />\r\nDinner is on your own then transfer to&nbsp;<strong>Lao Cai railway station for night train to Hanoi.</strong><br />\r\nOvernight on train ( Share 4 berth AC cabin).</p>\r\n', null, '52905cd70885e6c206185f2b3fa6420d.jpg', '2018-05-31 08:26:49', '2017-11-14 03:31:19', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('430', '81', '5', 'Hanoi – Halong Bay (B/L/D)', '<p>Arrival in Hanoi in the early morning, check in a hotel by the railway station for your refreshment and breakfast.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>08:00 - Meet our driver for a transfer to Halong via <strong>Bac Ninh and Sao D</strong>o. Extensive rice fields as far as your eyes can see will follow you along the way.<br />\r\n12:00 - Embarkation at <strong>Hon Gai port</strong>, relax with a welcome drink.<br />\r\n13:00 &ndash; Enjoy a seafood lunch on the boat while cruising in to the bay through the enchanting landscapes of <strong>Bai Tu Long Bay</strong> ( Small Dragon Bay).<br />\r\n15:30 - Take part in activities according to the boat such as: <strong>visit Thien Canh Son cave, go kayaking</strong>, take a <strong>bamboo sampan ride</strong> to the <strong>Vang Vieng fishing village</strong> or simply just relax on the boat.<br />\r\n18:00 - Return to the boat, shower and take a rest.<br />\r\n19:00 - Enjoy a delicious dinner on the boat.<br />\r\nStay overnight in a private cabin (with air conditioner and shower)</p>\r\n', null, '61645b3d8968ff67180fc9d54544a087.jpg', '2018-05-31 08:27:27', '2017-11-14 03:32:26', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('431', '81', '6', 'Halong – Hanoi – fly to Danang - Hoian (B/L-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">You are advised to get up early to enjoy the fresh air and sunrise in the beautiful scenery of <strong>Bai Tu Long.</strong><br />\r\nBreakfast on the boat.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n08:30 - Enjoy activities. Either <strong>visit the cave</strong> or embark a<strong> small bamboo sampan</strong> to visit Vung Vieng Fishing village, one of the spectacular floating villages in Halong. Encounter the locals and fishermen&rsquo;s farm as well as a floating school (depends on the boat&rsquo;s activity schedule)<br />\r\n09:30 - Return to the boat and check out of the cabin.<br />\r\n10:00 - Cruise back to <strong>Hon Gai port.</strong> On the way back, we will enjoy <strong>lunch on the boat.</strong> Last look at the legendary bay where dragons once descended.<br />\r\n11:45 - Arrive at the pier and transfer back to Hanoi&nbsp;and directly to airport for a <strong>short flight to Danang city.</strong><br />\r\nOn arrival, pick up and <strong>transfer to Hoian ancient town</strong>.<br />\r\nNote: Cruise&rsquo;s activities order will be depend on each cruises and tide. It is adjustable.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nOvernight in Hoian.</p>\r\n', null, '9fdf054f639f0e4ef0bfd766a7ddf5cc.jpg', '2018-05-31 08:29:33', '2017-11-14 19:40:58', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('432', '81', '7', 'Hoian Tour (B/-/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Enjoy a city tour in <strong>Hoian ancient town</strong> which is listed in the Heritage of Humans.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nSome real treasures that need to be discovered are <strong>Hoian Museum, Japanese bridge, China Town, Quan Thang ancient house</strong>, the <strong>local market </strong>and the <strong>old busy port</strong> of the 15th century for the international boats from China, Netherlands, Japan, and Poland.<br />\r\nFinally, visit the Thang Loi&nbsp;<strong>silk factory</strong>, known as a good establishment in Hoian to have tailor-made silk clothes.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn the evening,&nbsp;Embark on a <strong>small boat in Hoian town</strong> then depart to <strong>Thu Bon River</strong> which was once a very busy exchange place for a lot of international ships throughout the 15th century. The boat trip will take you along the river to <strong>Cua Dai sea gate</strong>. This is a good chance for you to appreciate the landscape of the peaceful village by the river bank and admire the fishermen&rsquo;s activities on the river. Enjoy the sunset in the late afternoon from April to November.<br />\r\nOvernight at Hoian.</p>\r\n', null, '92bc7b70bb246f1958d80295add3135c.jpg', '2018-05-31 08:29:08', '2017-11-14 03:35:04', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('433', '81', '8', 'Hoian – Danang – fly to Ho Chi Minh city ( Saigon) (B/-/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Transfer to Danang airport and take a <strong>morning flight to Saigon.</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nOn arrival, Meet our tour guide and driver and transfer to your hotel. Leave you luggage and enjoy a full day city tour.<br />\r\nVisit the <strong>Reunification palace</strong> (or the war memorials Museum), <strong>Notre Dame Cathedral</strong> and the <strong>Central Post Office</strong> inspired by Orsay Station in Paris.<br />\r\nThen, transfer to <strong>Cho Lon District </strong>to discover its <strong>old quarter</strong>, <strong>Binh Tay Market</strong> and the <strong>colorful Quan Am pagoda</strong>, one of the oldest pagodas in the city. Its architecture and decorations have remained since its construction.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nReturn to Saigon city for a <strong>walk in the city center</strong> visiting sites like the former<strong> Catinat streets</strong>, the <strong>Opera house</strong>, <strong>City Hall</strong> as well as <strong>Ben Thanh market.</strong><br />\r\nOvernight in Saigon.</p>\r\n', null, '0a2d6e5962022fb605c2f3f37903c805.jpg', '2018-05-31 08:29:54', '2017-11-14 03:35:43', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('434', '81', '9', 'Saigon – Cai Be – Can Tho (B/L/-) ', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Get picked up from your hotel and transfer to <strong>Cai Be</strong> ( 120km &ndash; 2.5 hour driving). Visit <strong>Cao Dai temple</strong> on route.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nUpon arrival, embark on a <strong>boat trip </strong>on a branch of the Mekong River to Vinh Long. Experience the rhythm of life on the l<strong>egendary Mekong River </strong>with a visit to <strong>Cai Be floating market </strong>and the <strong>orchid canals </strong>.<br />\r\nVisit crafts <strong>workshops </strong>of rice<strong>,</strong> popcorn, coconut caramel and rice cake.<br />\r\n<strong>Cycle or walk </strong>on the <strong>village paths</strong> to discover the ancient and beautiful <strong>Phu Chau pagoda</strong> where serenity reigns and meet the local people.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Enjoy &nbsp;lunch</strong> in an open air restaurant where you can taste a famous local specialty, the<strong> Elephant ear fish.</strong> Then enjoy <strong>tasting delicious fruits</strong> while rowing a <strong>small rowboat</strong> in the canals shaded by the fruit trees.<br />\r\nContinue your boat trip to <strong>Vinh Long</strong> and meet our driver at the pier for a<strong> transfer to Can Tho</strong>. Arrive in Can Tho in the late afternoon. &nbsp;Check in at your hotel and relax.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nEnjoy free time on your own to discover the city located on the Mekong River.<br />\r\nStay overnight in Can Tho.</p>\r\n', null, '5a1751ab1fd7a80c76df4d6432ddb9c6.jpg', '2018-06-27 04:36:34', '2017-11-14 03:36:26', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('435', '81', '10', 'Can Tho – Saigon (B/-/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Have breakfast at the hotel and<strong> transfer to the pier</strong> for a <strong>boat trip to visit Cai Rang floating market</strong>, the largest and most lively market in the Mekong Delta.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThere are so many colors and smells in the bubbling atmosphere where hundreds of sampans are filled with goods such as rice, fruits, and craft products. Everything is shown to sell from the early morning.<br />\r\nLeave the market and continue the<strong> boat trip through the canals</strong> and visit a fruit garden (Option - replace the garden with the nursery field by the river)<br />\r\nHead back to <strong>An Binh Market</strong> which is full of fish, fruits and vegetables.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nStop at <strong>Binh Thuy ancient house</strong> which contains the orchid garden where &ldquo;The Lover&rdquo; was filmed.<br />\r\nTransfer back to Saigon and arrive in the late afternoon.<br />\r\nOvernight in Saigon</p>\r\n', null, '9d9ccf023f9bf476a08d1c3772cbbca6.jpg', '2018-05-31 08:30:47', '2017-11-14 03:37:13', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('436', '81', '11', 'Saigon – Fly to Phnom Penh(B/-/D)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Free till meet our driver for a <strong>transfer to airport </strong>for a <strong>short international flight to Phnom Penh.</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nUpon arrival, our local tour guide will <strong>welcome </strong>you and transfer&nbsp;to the city center. Check in your hotel and enjoy a briefing tour as well as some first information about this beautiful region and visit the famous sites in the city:<br />\r\nStart with a visit to the <strong>impressive colorful Khmer-style royal palace</strong> complex built in 1866 by the Predecessors of King Norodom. Nearby is <strong>Silver pagoda </strong>(the emerald Buddha temple), which contains plenty of decorated Buddha Statues made of gold, diamond, gemstones and silver. Then visit the <strong>National Museum.</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nA <strong>welcome dinner</strong> will be served in the finest restaurant in the city.<br />\r\nOvernight in Phnom Penh.</p>\r\n', null, 'db3751e6ce1bc62dc9ca946e40a4076c.jpg', '2018-05-31 08:32:47', '2017-11-14 03:38:25', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('437', '81', '12', 'Phnom Penh city tour (B/-/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Have breakfast at your hotel, then spend a full day learning about the <strong>Khmer rouge</strong> in the past and Cambodia in the present.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn the morning, start to visit&nbsp;<strong>Choeung Ek museum</strong> or the<strong> Killing fields</strong>, where about 17 000 innocent Cambodian people (during1975 and 1978) including men, women, children and infants were detained and tortured at S-21 prison then transported for their extermination.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe continue to <strong>Tuol Sleng prison</strong>, now the <strong>Genocide Museum</strong>, the most secret part of the Khmer Rouge regime. It&rsquo;s also called<strong> S-21</strong> (abbreviated for Security Office 21), Khmer Rouge&#39;s premier security camp, specifically designed for the interrogation and extermination of anti-Angkor elements.<br />\r\nIt&#39;s surprising to know that S-21 used to be a high school before becoming this awful place during Khmer Rouge regime.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nReturn to the city to discover the local daily life at the <strong>Russian market</strong> and enjoy the bustling daily activities of the locals.&nbsp;<br />\r\nGo back to your hotel and relax.<br />\r\nNote: Please consider a different trip to the killing fields and S2-1 prison if you have small children in the group. We will offer other suitable alternative programs such as <strong>Koh Dach Island or Tamao wildlife </strong>rescue center.</p>\r\n', null, 'f34a695ba6ba58860b9b76c6f33abb20.jpg', '2018-05-31 08:33:53', '2017-11-14 03:40:37', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('438', '81', '13', 'Phnom Penh – Fly to Siem Reap – Rolous group – Banteay Srei (B/-/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Transfer to airport for <strong>flight to Siem Reap</strong>. Upon arrival, get a pick up and<strong> transfer to hotel</strong>. Check in your hotel and enjoy a briefing tour as well as some first information about this beautiful region.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nEnjoy a trip to <strong>Rolous Group</strong>. This is the ancient capital of King Indravarman I during 877AD &ndash; 889AD, also known as the birth place of the classical Khmer art and Architecture.<br />\r\nAmong the <strong>Roluos Group temples</strong>, there are some of the earliest permanent structures built by the Khmer empire, dating from the late 9th century. Some were totally built with bricks, others built with laterite or sandstone.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn the afternoon, visit<strong> Bantey Srei temple </strong>known as the <strong>Women&rsquo;s citadel </strong>and a cradle of the Angkor&rsquo;s finest stone carving.<br />\r\nThe temple is a masterpiece built with red sandstone.<br />\r\nReturn to Siem Reap and relax<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', null, '5912daff1202145888aeacdf670c23e9.jpg', '2018-05-31 08:34:51', '2017-11-14 03:41:46', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('439', '81', '14', 'Siem Reap – Angkor Thom – Taprohm – Angkor Wat (B/L/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">After breakfast at your hotel, meet our tour guide and enjoy a full day discovering the <strong>mysterious Angkor complex temples</strong>, starting from the <strong>South Gate of Angkor Thom</strong>, known as Big Angkor, the last capital of Angkor Empire surrounded by a wall and moat.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Bayon temple</strong> is in the heart of Angkor Thom. It is a special architecture with 54 towers and 4 smiling face statues. All are impressive bas-relief.&nbsp;<br />\r\nOur guide will lead you to the <strong>Terrace of Elephant</strong>. This is a terrace wall adorned with carved elephants Followed by <strong>Baphuon</strong> &ndash; a huge temple mountain and <strong>Terrace of the Leper King</strong> &ndash; a double wall carved with many mythological beings.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTraveling out of <strong>Angkor Thom</strong> and through the jungle will lead us to the sacred <strong>Ta Prohm temple</strong> ruin which is a great combination between human genius and natural beauty. Admire giant trees which have grown here for centuries. This is also the place where the &ldquo;Tomb Raider&rdquo; was filmed.<br />\r\nLunch will be served in the restaurant by the Srah Srang Lake.<br />\r\nIn the afternoon, discover<strong> Angkor Wat temple</strong>, the largest Khmer temple and the finest example of architecture and Angkorian art.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nEnjoy the <strong>sunset</strong> from the <strong>Phnom Bakeng</strong> hill before returning to your hotel for dinner and relaxation.<br />\r\nStay overnight in Siem Reap.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', null, '8c004001b36e23b38dd1be1af620f6fe.jpg', '2018-05-31 08:35:14', '2017-11-14 03:42:48', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('440', '81', '15', 'Siem Reap – floating Village – Flight to Luang Prabang (B/-/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Transfer to<strong> Tonle Sap Lake</strong>, located 10km from the city center. On arrival, <strong>embark a boat </strong>and discover the largest fresh water lake in Southeast Asia, known as one of the world&rsquo;s most varied and productive ecosystems the region that has always been of central importance for <strong>Cambodia&#39;s food provision.</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nDiscover the beauty of the water landscape and local life on the lake, visit a<strong> floating village</strong> and enjoy the encounters with the locals.<br />\r\nBack to hotel, check out and transfer to airport for your <strong>flight to Luang Prabang</strong><br />\r\nOn arrival, get a pick to hotel.<br />\r\n<strong>Overnight in Luang Prabang.</strong></p>\r\n', null, '6c73f54f76e2532c922ca7572b2709f8.jpg', '2018-05-31 08:35:47', '2017-11-14 03:44:09', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('441', '81', '16', 'Luang Prabang – City tour – Khuang Si Fall (B/-/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">After breakfast at your hotel, meet our tour guide and driver to go to <strong>Mount Phousi</strong> where you can enjoy a great panoramic view of the City and the river.<br />\r\nTake a short drive to <strong>Vat Xien Thong</strong> (the temple of Royal city). This is one of the most important Laotian monasteries and still remains a significant monument to the spirit of religion, traditional art and royalty.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe next&nbsp; stop will be <strong>Wat Visoun temple</strong>, dating back to 1513 and the reign of <strong>King Visoun</strong> . This is the oldest temple in Luang Prabang and was once the home to Luang Prabang Buddhas. <strong>Wat Visoun temple </strong>is with an unusual structure which represents the earliest Laotian style.<br />\r\nFollow this with a visit to <strong>Wat Mai</strong>, a beautiful temple built in the 18th century, located by the Royal palace. It is the biggest temple in Luang Prabang with beautiful decorations.<br />\r\nEnjoy a driving through rice fields and a beautiful small village. Make some stops to discover their daily life before reaching<strong> Khuang Si fall,</strong> a gorgeous turquoise waterfall. <strong>Refresh and swim</strong> in the clear water.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nReturn to city and spend the rest of day at your leisure.<br />\r\nStay overnight at a hotel in Luang Prabang.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', null, 'ccceee0527a1dfaf4a79e09ecb1c1584.jpg', '2018-05-31 08:40:46', '2017-11-14 03:45:08', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('442', '81', '17', 'Luang Prabang – Khmu Village – Wat Tham Xieng Maen (B/L/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">In the morning, meet our tour guide at your hotel and you cross the <strong>Mekong River </strong>via a local ferry towards <strong>Khmu village</strong>. En route, make a short visit to <strong>Ban Chan pottery village</strong>. It is a rare chance to try your hand at creating beautiful pots from clay.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAlong the way, you will pass through some <strong>rustic villages</strong>, encounter the local people, and see the children playing together or farmers doing their work on the fields. Visit<strong> Ban Boum Xieng</strong> to observe the ethnic traditions and daily life. Continue driving to a <strong>Khmu family</strong> and enjoy lunch with them.<br />\r\nIn the afternoon, drive back to the Mekong River and discover the decorative, less visited <strong>Wat Long Khun temple</strong>. From here, take a short transfer to <strong>Wat Tham Xieng Maen</strong> located in a limestone cave and visit its Buddha images.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe last highlight of the day is <strong>Wat Chom phet</strong> - This is an excellent spot for a panoramic view of the area as well as an excellent photo opportunity for a <strong>sunset photo hunter.</strong><br />\r\nReturn to your hotel and stay overnight in Luang Prabang.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', null, 'ba101a8d1d8697ddad084eef06f507fe.jpg', '2018-05-31 08:43:13', '2017-11-14 03:46:01', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('443', '81', '18', 'Luang Prabang – Pak Ou – Fly to Vientiane (B/-/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Have breakfast at your hotel then visit a <strong>local market</strong> in the town to discover the daily life. (We recommend visiting early in the morning).<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTransfer to the pier, embark a <strong>boat and enjoy a trip</strong> upstream along the Mekong River. Discover the <strong>numerous Buddha images in the Pak Oo caves </strong>such as <strong>Pak Oo cave</strong> (the mouth of the Oo River), <strong>Tham Ting cave</strong> ( Lower cave) and <strong>Tham Theung</strong> ( Upper cave). They are on the right side and overlook the Mekong River. Travel a short distance from the caves to the village of <strong>Ban Xang Hai</strong>.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nEncounter the locals and learn how to make LauLao (Laotian whisky) and <strong>LauHa</strong>i (Laotian wine). Return to the city, making stops at &nbsp;<strong>Ban Xang Khong village</strong> and <strong>Ban Xieng Lek village</strong>, well known for handmade <strong>Jute Sar paper</strong>.<br />\r\nBack to the city for the short <strong>flight to Vientiane</strong>, upon arrival, get a pick up to hotel.<br />\r\nOvernight in Vientiane.</p>\r\n', null, 'a295fd9c4f9e379407970942be7594be.jpg', '2018-05-31 08:43:50', '2017-11-14 03:48:03', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('444', '81', '19', 'Vientiane full day city tour (B/-/-)', '<p>Enjoy your breakfast at hotel and meet our tour guide for<strong> full day Vientiane city exploration.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The first highlight of the trip is <strong>Vat Phra Keo temple</strong>, built in 1565. It is one of the most interesting and impressive temples in Vientiane. It previously housed the famous <strong>Emerald Buddha image</strong>.<br />\r\nNext, visit <strong>Vat Sisaket temple</strong> which is well known for not only its cloister wall storing thousands of small Buddha images but also its beautiful architecture and decoration with dating back to 1818.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Transfer to visit <strong>Pha That Luang temple</strong>, built in 1566 and reconstructed in 1930. It is the most important Laotian religious and national monument. The temple has a special architecture reflecting the culture and identity of Laos, becoming a symbol of Laos nationalism.<br />\r\nLater, discover the<strong> Patuxay arc</strong>, a memorial monument built in 1957 and the most prominent landmark in the city. Its architecture was inspired by the &#39;<strong>Arc de Triumph&#39; in Paris</strong> combined with typical Laotian style. From the top of the monument, you can enjoy a great panoramic view of the city.<br />\r\nNext, move to <strong>Talat Sao market</strong> where you can do some shopping and uncover the local life.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the afternoon, visit the famous <strong>Buddha Park</strong>, located 25km from the city. The park is home to over <strong>200 Buddha statues</strong> and characters of Hinduism made from concrete, especially the enormous Buddha statue which is 40m in length propping its arm. Furthermore, there are many other statues you could visit to understand more about Buddhism.<br />\r\nStay overnight in Vientiane</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n', null, '22809dc661f0b7bfefced8912d314532.jpg', '2018-05-31 08:44:39', '2017-11-14 03:50:08', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('445', '81', '20', 'Vientiane – Departure (B/-/-)', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Free till meet our tour driver for a<strong> transfer to airport</strong> for your<strong> flight home </strong>or next destination.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTour ends.</p>\r\n', null, '1ead6a12e1197201481385041aca58e8.jpg', '2017-11-14 10:50:27', '2017-11-14 03:50:27', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('446', '82', '1', 'Saigon (Ho Chi Minh City) arrival (D)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Upon arrival, our <strong>Authentik Travel&rsquo;s tour guide and driver will welcome you</strong> and transfer to your hotel in the city center.<br />\r\nAfter briefing tour, our tour guide will give you some first information about our country and<strong> enjoy a welcome dinner</strong> at a finest restaurant.<br />\r\nOvernight in Saigon.</p>\r\n', null, '087f22778bebb724fb205cbf30e65a32.jpg', '2018-05-31 08:08:38', '2017-11-14 03:02:32', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('447', '82', '2', 'Saigon City Tour (B/L/-)', '<p>Meet our tour guide and driver at your htoel to enjoy a full day city tour.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Visit the <strong>Reunification palace</strong> (or the war memorials Museum), <strong>Notre Dame Cathedral</strong> and the <strong>Central Post Office</strong> inspired by Orsay Station in Paris.<br />\r\nThen, transfer to <strong>Cho Lon District </strong>to discover its <strong>old quarter</strong>, <strong>Binh Tay Market</strong> and the <strong>colorful Quan Am pagoda</strong>, one of the oldest pagodas in the city. Its architecture and decorations have remained since its construction.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nReturn to Saigon city for a <strong>walk in the city center</strong> visiting sites like the former<strong> Catinat streets</strong>, the <strong>Opera house</strong>, <strong>City Hall</strong> as well as <strong>Ben Thanh market.</strong><br />\r\nOvernight in Saigon.</p>\r\n', null, '709fdf53003a9bb83c9c7851e502ef68.jpg', '2018-05-31 08:09:00', '2017-11-14 03:03:17', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('448', '82', '3', 'Saigon – Cai Be – Can Tho (B/L/-) ', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Get picked up from your hotel and transfer to <strong>Cai Be</strong> ( 120km &ndash; 2.5 hour driving). Visit <strong>Cao Dai temple</strong> on route.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nUpon arrival, embark on a <strong>boat trip </strong>on a branch of the Mekong River to Vinh Long. Experience the rhythm of life on the l<strong>egendary Mekong River </strong>with a visit to <strong>Cai Be floating market </strong>and the <strong>orchid canals </strong>.<br />\r\nVisit crafts <strong>workshops </strong>of rice<strong>,</strong> popcorn, coconut caramel and rice cake.<br />\r\n<strong>Cycle or walk </strong>on the <strong>village paths</strong> to discover the ancient and beautiful <strong>Phu Chau pagoda</strong> where serenity reigns and meet the local people.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Enjoy &nbsp;lunch</strong> in an open air restaurant where you can taste a famous local specialty, the<strong> Elephant&nbsp;ear fish.</strong> Then enjoy <strong>tasting delicious fruits</strong> while rowing a <strong>small rowboat</strong> in the canals shaded by the fruit trees.<br />\r\nContinue your boat trip to <strong>Vinh Long</strong> and meet our driver at the pier for a<strong> transfer to Can Tho</strong>. Arrive in Can Tho in the late afternoon. &nbsp;Check in at your hotel and relax.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nEnjoy free time on your own to discover the city located on the Mekong River.<br />\r\nStay overnight in Can Tho.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', null, 'b06e13015c2055e8fce55b536d8863de.jpg', '2018-06-27 04:36:02', '2017-11-14 03:04:10', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('449', '82', '4', 'Can Tho – Saigon (B/-/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Have breakfast at the hotel and<strong> transfer to the pier</strong> for a <strong>boat trip to visit Cai Rang floating market</strong>, the largest and most lively market in the Mekong Delta.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThere are so many colors and smells in the bubbling atmosphere where hundreds of sampans are filled with goods such as rice, fruits, and craft products. Everything is shown to sell from the early morning.<br />\r\nLeave the market and continue the<strong> boat trip through the canals</strong> and visit a fruit garden (Option - replace the garden with the nursery field by the river)<br />\r\nHead back to <strong>An Binh Market</strong> which is full of fish, fruits and vegetables.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nStop at <strong>Binh Thuy ancient house</strong> which contains the orchid garden where &ldquo;The Lover&rdquo; was filmed.<br />\r\nTransfer back to Saigon and arrive in the late afternoon.<br />\r\nOvernight in Saigon<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', null, '9d9ccf023f9bf476a08d1c3772cbbca6.jpg', '2018-05-31 08:09:37', '2017-11-14 03:05:02', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('450', '82', '5', 'Saigon – fly to Danang – Hoian (B/-/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Transfer to airport for flight to Danang, pick up and transfer to <strong>Hoian ancient town.</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nEnjoy a city tour in <strong>Hoian ancient town</strong> which is listed in the Heritage of Humans.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nSome real treasures that need to be discovered are <strong>Hoian Museum, Japanese bridge, China Town, Quan Thang ancient house</strong>, the <strong>local market </strong>and the <strong>old busy port</strong> of the 15th century for the international boats from China, Netherlands, Japan, and Poland.<br />\r\nFinally, visit the Thang Loi&nbsp;<strong>silk factory</strong>, known as a good establishment in Hoian to have tailor-made silk clothes.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn the evening,&nbsp;Embark on a <strong>small boat in Hoian town</strong> then depart to <strong>Thu Bon River</strong> which was once a very busy exchange place for a lot of international ships throughout the 15th century. The boat trip will take you along the river to <strong>Cua Dai sea gate</strong>. This is a good chance for you to appreciate the landscape of the peaceful village by the river bank and admire the fishermen&rsquo;s activities on the river. Enjoy the sunset in the late afternoon from April to November.<br />\r\nOvernight at Hoian.</p>\r\n', null, '0a2d6e5962022fb605c2f3f37903c805.jpg', '2018-05-31 08:10:00', '2017-11-14 03:06:05', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('451', '82', '6', 'Hoian – Thanh Ha – Kim Bong villages (B/- /-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Get picked up from you hotel in Hoian Town and transfer to <strong>Thanh Ha village</strong>, located 2km from the town.<br />\r\nThe village is known for its pottery restoration activities and we can view the <strong>village&rsquo;s pottery</strong> in the ancient house in the town. There are still 23 families who have done <strong>pottery </strong>as their main job since the 16th century.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAfter the visit to Thanh Ha, we will discover the village&rsquo;s private <strong>porcelain museum.</strong><br />\r\nThen the <strong>boat trip</strong> will take us to <strong>Kim Bong village</strong>. On the boat, you will immerse yourselves into the comfortable fresh air and enjoy the idyllic landscapes on both sides of the river.<br />\r\nThis village has long been known for its <strong>wood carving</strong>. At first, the artisans inherited the techniques from the northern Vietnamese. Later, from business exchange, they could successfully adopt the know-how of Chinese and Japanese sculptures and cultivate their own style.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Stroll around the village</strong> to understand their daily life and visit a <strong>carpenter&#39;s workshop</strong> to admire their talent. It is possible to buy some wood products for your souvenirs.<br />\r\nReturn to Hoian town by boat.</p>\r\n', null, 'e7ac77a84c82362af233e2d154b41d1e.jpg', '2018-05-31 08:13:04', '2017-11-14 03:07:20', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('452', '82', '7', 'Hoian – Hue (B/-/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Depart from <strong>Hoian ancient town to Hue</strong>. Drive along the coastline and arrive in Danang. Enjoy a walk to <strong>My Khe beach</strong> where you can enjoy the view of giant Goodness of Mercy statues in the <strong>Linh Ung Pagoda</strong>. Take photos of fishermen by the beach and visit the <strong>Cham Museum </strong>which preserves the most important Cham culture collections in the world.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nContinue to Hue on the <strong>Mandarin Road </strong>via <strong>Sea Cloud Pass </strong>(Hai Van Pass). Stop on the top of the pass to enjoy the breathtaking view to the ocean and Da Nang city.<br />\r\nArrive in Hue and check in to your hotel.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', null, '02a058986b6bdcc8c06cc684d77a182e.jpg', '2018-05-31 08:13:46', '2017-11-14 03:08:15', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('453', '82', '8', 'Hue – Discovery (B/-/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Transfer to the pier by the <strong>Perfume River bank</strong> to embark a <strong>Royal boat trip</strong> to the villages in the East of the city. This is an opportunity to discover the local life on the both sides of this poetic river.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nUpon arrival in <strong>Tien Nom village</strong>, disembark for a<strong> bike ride</strong> (or&nbsp; motorbike) in the countryside through three villages: <strong>Tien Nom, Thanh Tien and Sinh village.</strong> &nbsp;The trip will immerse you into the daily rhythm of life in the villages.<br />\r\nIn Tien Non Village, meet the villagers working on the fields and vegetable gardens. Then, visit a family worship house in the village.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nNext, reach <strong>Thanh Tien village,</strong> an artificial paper flower village dating back 400 years. Besides the rural works, they make paper flowers for the New Year festival to offer their ancestors the best wishes. Visit Mr. Hieu&rsquo;s family, one of the well-known artisans in the village to learn how to make paper flowers under his instruction.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nKeep going to <strong>Sinh Village,</strong> a cradle of 400 year folklore prints in Hue. Meet Mr. Phuoc who will explain the techniques of traditional prints. You will find beautiful souvenirs on this trip.<br />\r\nFinally, take the boat back to the city.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn the afternoon, visit <strong>Thien Mu Pagoda</strong>, &nbsp;one of the oldest pagodas in Hue, dating back to 1601. This is the spiritual highlight of the city and well known for its majestic octagon tower and beautiful view of the Perfume River.<br />\r\nThen, continue to the most anticipated site in Hue, Hue citadel, the only vestige symbol for what was once the imperial city of Vietnam. It is inspired by the fortification of Vauban. The city is composed of three parts: Kinh Thanh (<strong>the Capital city</strong>), Hoang Thanh (t<strong>he Imperial city</strong>) and Cam Thanh (<strong>the Forbidden City</strong>). The most beautiful sites in Hue are concentrated in this area including the flag tower, the South gate, the palace of supreme Harmony, the Dynasty temple area and the settlement area. During the visit, we will attend a <strong>traditional dancing show</strong> in the royal theater.<br />\r\nBack to your hotel in the late afternoon.</p>\r\n', null, '039d3eb69512d0b738035daa85747c92.jpg', '2018-05-31 08:16:00', '2017-11-14 03:09:56', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('454', '82', '9', 'Hue – Minh Mang – Boat trip to Thuy Bieu Village – Fly to Hanoi (B/L/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">At 8.00, transfer upstream of the <strong>Perfume river</strong> to visit the emperor,<strong> Minh Mang&#39;s tomb</strong>, an architectural masterpiece that harmoniously highlights the nature and imperial religious works.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAfter that, we will voyage along the Perfume River to <strong>Thuy Bieu Village</strong> taking in the picturesque landscapes on both sides. After 1 hour, we arrive in Thuy Bieu known for its divine grapefruit trees where you can take a bike around the village under the shade of the grapefruit trees and enjoy their pleasant perfume aroma and the harvested straw. The peaceful atmosphere is in every corner of the village.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThen, <strong>visit a temple</strong> dedicated to the village protector, a traditional garden house built several centuries ago. This is a wonderful opportunity to stop for great photos and interact with the villagers working in the gardens and vegetable fields which should not be missed.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Lunch is served at Mrs. Loan</strong> in the village of Thuy Bieu.<br />\r\nIn the afternoon, take a <strong>short flight to Hanoi</strong>. On arrival, our tour guide and driver will welcome you and transfer to your hotel in the city center.<br />\r\nOvernight in Hanoi.</p>\r\n', null, '7f71f8ae3c078ef8d34722d619a7e8ac.jpg', '2018-05-31 08:18:15', '2017-11-14 03:10:56', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('455', '82', '10', 'Hanoi city tour (B/-/-)', '<p>Today, we discover the wonders of the <strong>capital of Vietnam</strong>, filled with timeless charm. Start by visiting <strong>Van Mieu (Temple of Literature)</strong>, the first University of Vietnam built from the 11th century by Emperor Ly Thanh Tong. Continue to visit <strong>Chua Ha (Ha Pagoda)</strong>, known as a sacred place to pray for luck in love, especially for your future spouse.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAfter that, transfer to the<strong> Ethnology Museum</strong> (closed every Monday) which offers a deep insight into Vietnamese culture through traditional costumes, tools, musical instruments and traditional houses of many minority ethnic groups. Enjoy a special<strong> water puppet show in the museum garden.</strong><br />\r\n<strong>Lunch </strong>is served in a local restaurant.<br />\r\nIn the afternoon, discover the <strong>Ho Chi Minh complex</strong> including the <strong>Presidential Palace, Ho Chi Minh&#39;s House on stilts and the fish pond</strong>.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor those who are interested in visiting the <strong>Ho Chi Minh Mausoleum</strong>, it is only open in the morning and closed every Monday and Friday. Sometimes it is necessary to queue for a couple of hours to go inside the mausoleum.<br />\r\nTransfer to the old quarter to visit Hoan Kiem lake (Restored Sword Lake) and Ngoc Son temple in the middle of the lake.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Return to your hotel in the late afternoon.</p>\r\n', null, '966010a786f329b6420055b7f46dc2e5.jpg', '2018-05-31 08:18:50', '2017-11-14 03:11:53', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('456', '82', '11', 'Hanoi – Halong (B/L/D)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">8.30am, pick up and&nbsp;<strong>transfer to Halong Bay</strong><br />\r\n12h30 &ndash; 13h00&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>&nbsp;Embark Cruise</strong>&nbsp;followed by a short cruise briefing.<br />\r\n13h30 &ndash; 14h30&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Savor a&nbsp;<strong>delectable lunch on cruises&nbsp;</strong>among the limestone islands.<br />\r\n15h00 &ndash; 16h00&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>Explore the amazing Sung Sot Cave</strong>&nbsp;&ndash; the most beautiful cave in Halong Bay.<br />\r\n16h00 &ndash; 17h00&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Cruising to<strong>&nbsp;Titov island</strong>. Go swimming and relaxing&nbsp;<strong>at the beach of Titov or climb up to the top of the island&nbsp;</strong>for a panorama view of Halong Bay.<br />\r\n17h00 &ndash; 17h30&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Return to the main boat and continue&nbsp;<strong>cruising to the quiet area&nbsp;</strong>while enjoy<strong>&nbsp;beautiful seascape on the way</strong>.<br />\r\n17h30 &ndash; 19h00&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Enjoy Sunset Party on sundeck</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong>admire the best moments of the day when the sun starts to set.</strong><br />\r\n19h00&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>Dinner is served.</strong>&nbsp;Socialize with other guests, take part in board games, fish for squid, or just laze around.<br />\r\nOvernight on board.</p>\r\n', null, '404ce1645985aa4541811fd35a98a565.jpg', '2018-05-31 08:19:42', '2017-11-14 03:12:30', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('457', '82', '12', 'Halong – Hanoi – Fly to Siem Reap (B/L/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">06h30 &ndash; 07h00&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Start your day with<strong>&nbsp;Tai Chi exercises or a photo hunt.</strong><br />\r\n07h00 &ndash; 07h30&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Have breakfast on board and enjoy the peaceful morning of Halong Bay.<br />\r\n08h30 &ndash; 09h30&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>Kayak among the hidden areas</strong>&nbsp;of the bay, around the&nbsp;<strong>Drum Cave</strong>.<br />\r\n09h45 Return to the boat. Freshen up and check out of your cabin.<br />\r\n10h00 &ndash; 10h30&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Continue your cruise exploring the Bay, passing&nbsp;<strong>Ba Hang fishing village, Dog Islet,</strong>&nbsp;and more.<br />\r\n10h30 &ndash; 11h30&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; While heading&nbsp;<strong>back to the harbor</strong>, watch the fruit carving demonstration and participate in the&nbsp;<strong>Cooking Class&nbsp;</strong>before&nbsp;<strong>enjoying a traditional Vietnamese lunch.</strong><br />\r\n11h45 &ndash; 12h00&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Disembark the cruise and take a transfer back to Hanoi and directly to airport for a <strong>short flight to &nbsp;Siem Reap.</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nUpon arrival, our local&nbsp;tour guide will <strong>welcome you at small charming Siem Reap international airport</strong> and transfer a short distance to the down town. Check in your hotel and enjoy a briefing tour as well as some first information about this beautiful region.<br />\r\nOvernight in Siem Reap.</p>\r\n', null, 'c97f95e811e30cec0a958f27822cba4a.jpg', '2018-05-31 08:20:24', '2017-11-14 19:41:40', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('458', '82', '13', 'Siem Reap – Angkor Thom – Taprohm – Angkor Wat (B/L/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">After breakfast at your hotel, meet our tour guide and enjoy a full day discovering the <strong>mysterious Angkor complex temples</strong>, starting from the <strong>South Gate of Angkor Thom</strong>, known as Big Angkor, the last capital of Angkor Empire surrounded by a wall and moat.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Bayon temple</strong> is in the heart of Angkor Thom. It is a special architecture with 54 towers and 4 smiling face statues. All are impressive bas-relief.&nbsp;<br />\r\nOur guide will lead you to the <strong>Terrace of Elephant</strong>. This is a terrace wall adorned with carved elephants Followed by <strong>Baphuon</strong> &ndash; a huge temple mountain and <strong>Terrace of the Leper King</strong> &ndash; a double wall carved with many mythological beings.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTraveling out of <strong>Angkor Thom</strong> and through the jungle will lead us to the sacred <strong>Ta Prohm temple</strong> ruin which is a great combination between human genius and natural beauty. Admire giant trees which have grown here for centuries. This is also the place where the &ldquo;Tomb Raider&rdquo; was filmed.<br />\r\nLunch will be served in the restaurant by the Srah Srang Lake.<br />\r\nIn the afternoon, discover<strong> Angkor Wat temple</strong>, the largest Khmer temple and the finest example of architecture and Angkorian art.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nEnjoy the <strong>sunset</strong> from the <strong>Phnom Bakeng</strong> hill before returning to your hotel for dinner and relaxation.<br />\r\nStay overnight in Siem Reap.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', null, '66e34926903715951fa924afd5555d16.jpg', '2018-05-31 08:21:10', '2017-11-14 03:14:48', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('459', '82', '14', 'Siem Reap – Rolous Group – Banteay Srei (B/-/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Meet our tour guide and driver at your hotel and enjoy a trip to <strong>Rolous Group</strong>. This is the ancient capital of King Indravarman I during 877AD &ndash; 889AD, also known as the birth place of the classical Khmer art and Architecture.<br />\r\nAmong the <strong>Roluos Group temples</strong>, there are some of the earliest permanent structures built by the Khmer empire, dating from the late 9th century. Some were totally built with bricks, others built with laterite or sandstone.<br />\r\nIn the afternoon, visit<strong> Bantey Srei temple </strong>known as the <strong>Women&rsquo;s citadel </strong>and a cradle of the Angkor&rsquo;s finest stone carving.<br />\r\nThe temple is a masterpiece built with red sandstone.<br />\r\nReturn to Siem Reap and relax<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', null, 'c22463378450a3c42322e9233439c565.jpg', '2018-05-31 08:21:33', '2017-11-14 03:15:40', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('460', '82', '15', 'Siem Reap – floating Village (B/-/-)', '<p>Transfer to<strong> Tonle Sap Lake</strong>, located 10km from the city center. On arrival, <strong>embark a boat </strong>and discover the largest fresh water lake in Southeast Asia, known as one of the world&rsquo;s most varied and productive ecosystems the region that has always been of central importance for <strong>Cambodia&#39;s food provision.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Discover the beauty of the water landscape and <strong>local life on the lake</strong>, visit a<strong> floating village</strong> and enjoy the encounters with the locals.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Back to hotel</strong> and free to relax in the afternoon or discover the <strong>local Siem Reap market </strong>for your souvenirs before going home.<br />\r\nOvernight in Siem Reap.</p>\r\n', null, '39bef9b923bfaad8ca00dd70615a791d.jpg', '2018-05-31 08:23:24', '2017-11-14 03:16:21', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('461', '82', '16', 'Siem Reap – Departure (B/-/-)', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Free till <strong>transfer to airport</strong> for <strong>your flight home</strong> or next destinations.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTour ends.</p>\r\n', null, '13779a2bb9304195e29c509cd83aea66.jpg', '2017-11-14 10:16:43', '2017-11-14 03:16:43', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('463', '83', '2', 'Yangon – Twante – Dala full day (B/L/-)', '<p>Meet our tour guide at your hotel and <strong>transfer to Twante</strong>. Once out of the city, you will feel the contrast with Yangon. There&#39;s no noise or traffic, only peaceful rice fields. Sometimes, you will be able to see the local villages and small pagodas along the way.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Make a stop to visit the <strong>Paung Taw Choke Pagoda</strong> or simply <strong>Pythons pagoda</strong>, located in the middle of a pond. You will see real pythons sleeping in every corner of pagoda. Enjoy the peaceful moment while feeding the fish in the pond.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The next stop will be <strong>Shwe San Daw Pagoda</strong>, the biggest in this area, before visiting the traditional handicraft pottery families in Twante. You will see the ancestral way to make pottery. Everything made by hand without machinery or electrical support.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After that, visit the <strong>weaving textile factory</strong> at <strong>Shan Su village</strong>, the ancient moat and the city wall as well as exploring the<strong> local Twante market</strong>. This is a chance to experience the local life.<br />\r\nHave lunch in <strong>Twante town</strong> before traveling close to the Yangon river bank to uncover Dala village, near Yangon. Here, you will see the very different life from Yangon.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Take a<strong> trishaw to visit the villages</strong> and then take a ferry to cross the river to Yangon.&nbsp;<br />\r\nFrom the pier, <strong>walk through the colonial streets</strong> or take &nbsp;a taxi back to your hotel.<br />\r\nStay overnight in Yangon.</p>\r\n', null, 'e561ac08ea64cb306a2ead914b00d330.jpg', '2018-05-16 10:41:08', '2017-11-12 21:05:12', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('464', '83', '3', 'Yangon – Golden Rock (B/-/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Meet our tour guide and driver at your hotel and transfer for couple of hours through the beautiful, rural landscapes to <strong>Kyaikto town.</strong><br />\r\nTurn left to reach <strong>Kinpun town</strong>. From there, change trucks for a 1 hour transfer to the top of the mountain where the <strong>Golden Rock Pagoda</strong> is located. &nbsp;<br />\r\nAt the top, you will have time to discover the <strong>sacred golden rock</strong> covered with gold leaves pasted on by its male devotees.<br />\r\nTake time to relax and enjoy the fantastic <strong>views of the splendid mountain ranges</strong> before taking a rest in a hotel at the top.<br />\r\nStay overnight at the Golden Rock.</p>\r\n', null, 'de195e67d1b65384b8d6c2cda5f7f55c.jpg', '2018-05-16 10:41:25', '2017-11-12 21:05:52', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('465', '83', '4', 'Golden Rock – Bago visit – Yangon (B/-/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Get up early to see the <strong>sunrise over the mountains</strong> and enjoy the fresh air and tranquility before your breakfast.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTransfer<strong> back to Kinpun</strong> by truck. From there, meet our driver and transfer back to Yangon by car.&nbsp;<br />\r\nOn the way, do not miss the <strong>Bago</strong>, also known as<strong> Pegu</strong>. Stop to discover the <strong>Reclining Shwethalyaung Buddha</strong>, the four seated Buddha at Kyaikpun Pagoda and the old <strong>Kambozathadi</strong> palace built for King Bayinnaung in 1556, consisting of 76 apartments and halls. Also visit the <strong>Shwemawdaw Pagoda</strong>, the most beautiful religious monument in Bago. It is located at a higher altitude than the Shwedagon pagoda in Yangon and can be seen from 10km away.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nExplore the <strong>Bago local market</strong> before driving back to Yangon.<br />\r\nOn arrival, relax at your hotel and stay overnight in Yangon.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', null, 'b370046c78fe064ca6fb6341f8252fa3.jpg', '2018-05-16 10:41:44', '2017-11-12 21:06:41', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('466', '83', '5', 'Yangon city tour – Departure (B/-/-)', '<p>Starting from your hotel, visit the <strong>colonial style buildings</strong>. Walk along the streets to enjoy the beauty of these historic buildings, built last century and following<strong> British architecture</strong>. Then, visit the famous landmarks in the city such as <strong>Sule Pagoda</strong>, built in the 3rd century and located right in the city center.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The next landmark is<strong> Botahtaung pagoda </strong>by the grand Yangon River. According to the locals, the pagoda was built over 2000 years ago and enshrined by the sacred relics of the Buddha.<br />\r\nEnjoy lunch at a recommended local restaurant.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the late afternoon, visit <strong>Scott market or Bogyoke market</strong> (closed on Monday) selling the medicines, foodstuffs, garments, electrics, souvenirs, jewelry, and art to witness the local way of life.&nbsp;<br />\r\nTransfer to airport for flight home.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTour ends.</p>\r\n', null, '5f1e74849c0cf4ae21b553831dee4e4a.jpg', '2018-05-16 10:42:12', '2017-11-12 21:07:40', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('467', '84', '1', 'Yangon arrival – City tour (-/-/D)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Upon arrival in Yangon airport, Authentik Travel&rsquo;s tour guide and driver will <strong>welcome you</strong> and <strong>transfer to hotel</strong> in the city center.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nLeave your luggage at hotel and discover the highlights of the city:<br />\r\nexplore the <strong>Chaukhtatgyi Buddha temple</strong> which houses one of the most revered reclining Buddha images in the country. It is the most well-known Buddhist temple in Bahan township of Yangon and is also one of the biggest Buddhas in Myanmar. The reclining Buddha image is 66 meters long and was built during the 1900&#39;s.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFollow this with a visit to the 2500 year old magnificent <strong>Shwedagon pagoda</strong>, the most famous and sacred place of Myanmar. In the middle is a huge bell shaped stupa, plated with tons of gold and thousands of diamonds and rubies decorating the top of the stupa. The pagoda is surrounded by other shrines, temples and many other religious structures inside it. The <strong>sunset from the Pagoda</strong> should not be missed.<br />\r\nEnjoy a welcome dinner at a finest local restaurant.<br />\r\nStay overnight in Yangon.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', null, '9dfd554532244a66c3dc68d639bc048b.jpg', '2018-05-16 10:30:21', '2017-11-12 20:56:19', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('468', '84', '2', 'Yangon – Fly to Bagan full day tour (B/-/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Transfer to airport for <strong>morning flight to Bagan.</strong><br />\r\nArrive in Bagan in the morning and be greeted by our local tour guide and driver at airport, then transfer to your hotel in the area. Leave your luggage at the hotel and enjoy a full day trip to discover this tranquil area.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nHead to <strong>Swhezigon pagoda</strong> before the hottest part of the day. This is the gold plated pagoda built to house the Buddhist relic brought from India a thousand years ago.<br />\r\nThe next stop is a short visit to discover <strong>Nyaung U market</strong>. A bustling market where locals meet to exchange<strong> fruits,</strong> <strong>vegetables, lacquerware and &nbsp;pottery</strong>.<br />\r\nAfter the market, visit<strong> Gubyaukgyi Temple</strong>, famous for its mural. Our guide will translate the great story from the ancient pictures on the wall.<br />\r\nEnjoy lunch and relax at your hotel.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn the afternoon, visit the <strong>Ananda temples</strong> built in 1105 AD, home to four standing Buddhas, each one facing the cardinal directions of North, West, East and South. &nbsp;Then visit Htilominlo temple to admire the four Buddhas that face each direction.&nbsp;<br />\r\nEnd of the day at <strong>Shwesandaw temple</strong> and enjoy the <strong>sunset over the mountains.</strong><br />\r\nStay overnight in Bagan<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', null, 'b6f4599c7eb63385e19621b2e6f170f1.jpg', '2018-05-16 10:31:39', '2017-11-12 20:58:15', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('469', '84', '3', 'Bagan – Fly to Mandalay– Full day tour (B/-/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Transfer from your hotel to Bagan airport for short <strong>flight to Mandalay.</strong><br />\r\nUpon arrival in Mandalay in the morning, meet our tour guide at the airport and enjoy a full day tour of the city before check in at your hotel.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nOn the way from airport, we will turn left over a bridge and head to <strong>Sagaing hill </strong>where a lot of Buddhist monasteries are situated.<br />\r\nSagaing is a hill terrace, so from this site you can view the great Ayeyarwaddy River, and Mandalay city with its numerous <strong>temples and monasteries</strong>. The major attraction on Sagaing hill is <strong>U Min Thoze pagoda.</strong><br />\r\nNext to Visit <strong>Mahamuni Pagoda</strong>, a <strong>marble sculpture</strong>, to see how local people make Buddha statues from marble, the<strong> gold leaf making center</strong>, and the <strong>Shwenandaw monastery</strong>, or <strong>Golden Monastery</strong>, well known for its great wood carvings. Also, visit <strong>Kuthodaw pagoda</strong>, known as the biggest book in the world, with 729 marble slabs inscribed with the Buddha&rsquo;s doctrine.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTake in the<strong> beautiful sunse</strong>t from the top of Mandalay hill.<br />\r\nOvernight in Mandalay city.</p>\r\n', null, '6a62fd02244dd50a1380aa544629e014.jpg', '2018-05-16 10:35:28', '2017-11-12 20:59:02', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('470', '84', '4', 'Mandalay – Fly to Heho – Inle lake (B/-/-)', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Transfer to Mandalay airport for <strong>flight to Heho in the morning.</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nUpon arrival at Heho airport, meet our tour guide and driver for 1 hour transfer to <strong>Nyaungshwe town</strong>. This drive will offer you delightful scenery of the hill station region, passing by the picturesque landscapes along the way.<br />\r\nCheck in at your hotel in the town by the lake and embark on a boat trip in the huge lake to enjoy the beautiful landscapes and see the local <strong>Intha people </strong>working on the lake. They skillfully stand and r<strong>ow the boat with 1 leg, </strong>a truly unique way to row a boat.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nPass the<strong> floating gardens</strong> on the lake and listen as the guide tells you about the lifestyle, culture and how they cultivate their vegetation as well as the way they catch fish in the lake with their traditional traps.<br />\r\nExplore the<strong> Nampan villages</strong> at the end of Inle Lake and visit their traditional handicraft villages such as <strong>silk weaving lotus, cigarette and boat making</strong> as well as the <strong>blacksmith village.</strong><br />\r\nReturn to <strong>Nyaungshwe town</strong> and stay overnight.<br />\r\nNote: An overnight stay at the resort on Inle Lake is available on request.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', null, '1b45b219fa14e6a6d2e42cbbf4d063eb.jpg', '2018-05-16 10:35:51', '2017-11-12 21:00:01', '5', '5');
INSERT INTO au_tourdetail VALUES ('471', '84', '5', 'Heho – Tour – fly to Yangon in the late afternoon (B/-/-)', '<p>Get picked up from your hotel and visit a <strong>5 day rotational local market</strong>. This is the most fascinating way to explore the daily life of the <strong>ethnic minority groups</strong>. Continue the <strong>boat trip</strong> to<strong> Indein Pagoda</strong>.<br />\r\nThe boat will leave the lake and enter a small canal. After 30 minutes, arrive in <strong>Pa O tribe village</strong>. From the village, take a walk through the old cover path to hundreds of <strong>pagoda ruins</strong>. The main stupa on top of the hill offers gorgeous views over the surrounding mountain ranges and the lake in distance.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Walk back to the jetty and embark on the<strong> boat to the Lake.</strong> &nbsp;On the way, make stop at the <strong>long neck women&#39;s village</strong> and their silk shop, <strong>Phaung Daw OO pagoda</strong> (Jumping Cat pagoda) before returning to your hotel in Nyangshwe town and transfer to airport for a<strong> flight to Yangon</strong>.<br />\r\nOn arrival, get a pick up to hotel.<br />\r\nStay overnight in Yangon.</p>\r\n', null, 'cf9d111d0321b38541f1856d537f7058.jpg', '2018-05-16 10:36:20', '2017-11-12 21:02:13', '5', '5');
